'''Edem Adzaho''' is a trainer, author, public speaker and [[Ghana]]ian [[Human resource consulting|human resource consultant]]. She was voted 17th on the 2015 Most Influential Young Ghanaian list.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://thebftonline.com/lifestyle/16977/edem-adzaho-gets-another-feather-in-her-cap-places-17th-on-most-influential-young-ghanaian-and-ready-to-take-on-the-world.html|title=Edem Adzaho gets another feather in her cap ...places 17th on Most Influential Young Ghanaian and ready to take on the world|last=|first=|date=|website=thebftonline.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630143405/https://thebftonline.com/lifestyle/16977/edem-adzaho-gets-another-feather-in-her-cap-places-17th-on-most-influential-young-ghanaian-and-ready-to-take-on-the-world.html|archive-date=2012-06-30|dead-url=yes|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref>

== Career ==
Edem consults for the [[British Council]] in Ghana. She has held positions such as Intercultural Fluency Master Trainer, External Consultant and has served on the assessment board for selecting Ghanaians for the [[Tullow Oil|Tullow Group Scholarship Scheme]] which was facilitated by the British Council since 2012 until it was ended in 2016. Tullow Oil's flagship scheme was dedicated to giving young Ghanaians the opportunity to benefit from the country's recently discovered oil resources.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/business/2014/September-6th/50-students-get-tullow-oil-scholarship.php|title=50 students get Tullow Oil Scholarship|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Myjoyonline.com|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tullowoil.com/media/case-studies/tullow-group-scholarship-scheme|title=Tullow Group Scholarship Scheme|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2015/09/12/tullow-offers-scholarship-to-41-ghanaians/|title=Tullow offers scholarship to 41 Ghanaians|last=Blay|first=Pius Amihere|date=2015-09-12|website=Ghana News|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref> She is an external facilitator for the University of Ghana Business School's Centre for Management and Professional Development.<ref name=":0" /> She has written two books: ''Your Degree Will Never Be Enough'' and ''The Global Graduates''.<ref name=":0" /> She was a speaker for [[TED (conference)|TEDxAccra]] in 2016.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2016/04/18/tedxaccra-speaker-profile-edem-adzaho/|title=TEDxAccra speaker profile - Edem Adzaho|last=Adogla-Bessa|first=Delali|date=2016-04-18|website=Ghana News|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref>

