'''Paris Whitney Hilton''' (born February 17, 1981)<ref name=filmref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/88/Paris-Hilton.html|title=Paris Hilton Biography (1981-)|publisher=FilmReference.com|accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref> is an American media personality, socialite, businesswoman, model, singer, DJ, author and actress. She is the great-granddaughter of [[Conrad Hilton]], the founder of [[Hilton Hotels & Resorts|Hilton Hotels]]. Born in [[New York City]] and raised there and in [[Beverly Hills, California]], Hilton began her modeling career as a teenager when she signed with New York-based modeling development agency [[Trump Model Management]]. Her lifestyle made her a feature of entertainment news and tabloid magazines, and Hilton was proclaimed "New York's leading [[It girl]]" in 2001.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.biography.com/people/paris-hilton-11271420?page=1|title=Paris Hilton Biodata|publisher=Biography.com|accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> In 2003, a [[Celebrity sex tape|sex tape]] with Hilton and her then-boyfriend [[Rick Salomon]], later released as ''[[1 Night in Paris]]'', was leaked to the public. Released only three weeks before the premiere of the reality television series ''[[The Simple Life]]'', in which she starred alongside her long-time friend [[Nicole Richie]], the sex tape became a media sensation.

In 2004, Hilton released her book ''[[Confessions of an Heiress]]'', which became a [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''New York Times'' Best Seller]], in 2005, she appeared in the horror film ''[[House of Wax (2005 film)|House of Wax]]'', and in 2006, her self-titled album, ''[[Paris (Paris Hilton album)|Paris]]'', was released worldwide; it reached number six on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Paris Hilton's Music|url=http://www.parishiltonsite.net/music.php|publisher=Parishiltonsite.net|accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> with her debut single, "[[Stars Are Blind]]", quickly becoming a hit around the world. Hilton returned to reality television in 2008 with ''[[Paris Hilton's My New BFF]]'' and its two [[Spin-off (media)|spin-offs]]: ''[[Paris Hilton's British Best Friend]]'' (2009) and ''[[Paris Hilton's Dubai BFF]]'' (2009), and again in 2011, with [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] series ''[[The World According to Paris]]''. Her big-screen credits include the films ''[[Raising Helen]]'' (2004), ''[[Bottoms Up (2006 film)|Bottoms Up]]'' (2006), ''[[National Lampoon's Pledge This!]]'' (2006), ''[[Repo! The Genetic Opera]]'' (2008), and [[Sofia Coppola]]'s film ''[[The Bling Ring]]'' (2013) as well as the documentaries ''[[Paris, Not France]]'' (2008), ''[[Teenage Paparazzo]]'' (2010) and ''[[The American Meme]]'' (2018).

In 2012, Hilton made her debut as a [[Disc jockey|DJ]] at the [[São Paulo]] Pop Music Festival. Initially panned by critics, she has become one of the highest-paid celebrity DJs, and between 2013 and 2017, held the "Paris Hilton: Foam & Diamonds"  residence at the [[Amnesia (nightclub)|Amnesia nightclub]] in [[Ibiza]]. She signed a record deal with [[Cash Money Records]] in 2013,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/oct/23/paris-hilton-earns-up-to-1m-single-dj-set|title=Paris Hilton earns up to $1 million per DJ set|date=October 23, 2014|work=[[theguardian.com]]|publisher=theguardian|accessdate=October 23, 2014}}</ref> and has since released the singles "[[Good Time (Paris Hilton song)|Good Time]]" (2013), "[[Come Alive (Paris Hilton song)|Come Alive]]" (2014), "[[High Off My Love]]" (2015), and "[[I Need You (Paris Hilton song)|I Need You]]" (2018).

Credited with influencing the revival of the [[famous for being famous]] phenomenon during the early and mid 2000s,<ref name="phfame">{{cite web|url=http://www.scoreboard-media.com/paris-hilton-rule/ |title=The Paris Hilton Rule: Famous For Being Famous |work=Scoreboard Media Group |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120528065137/http://www.scoreboard-media.com/paris-hilton-rule/ |archivedate=May 28, 2012 }}</ref> Hilton exemplifies the "[[celebutante]]", a celebrity not through talent or work, but through inherited wealth and lifestyle. She has parlayed her media fame into perfumes and various lines with her [[testimonial|endorsement]]; her [[list of celebrity-branded perfumes|perfume brand]] alone have brought in over US$2.5 billion in revenue, the second largest celebrity fragrance of all time behind Hollywood actress [[Elizabeth Taylor]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kafkaesqueblog.com/2013/11/17/celebrities-best-selling-fragrances-sales-figures-the-perfume-industry|title=Celebrities best selling fragrances in the perfume industry |date=October 2, 2015|work=Kafkaequeblog.com|publisher=Kafkaequeblog|accessdate=November 13, 2013}}</ref><ref name="pearns">{{cite news|title=SURPRISE? Paris Hilton Earns Over $10M A Year From 17 Different Product Lines |url=http://articles.businessinsider.com/2011-06-01/entertainment/30076238_1_piers-morgan-paris-hilton-product-lines |publisher=Articles.businessinsider.com |accessdate=July 31, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020044952/http://articles.businessinsider.com/2011-06-01/entertainment/30076238_1_piers-morgan-paris-hilton-product-lines |archivedate=October 20, 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref name="phe">{{cite news|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2011-05-31/entertainment/piers.morgan.paris.hilton_1_hotel-heiress-paris-hilton-rick-salomon/2?_s=PM:SHOWBIZ |title=Paris Hilton on sex tape: 'I'll never be able to erase it' |publisher=CNN |accessdate=July 31, 2012 |date=February 15, 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009020555/http://articles.cnn.com/2011-05-31/entertainment/piers.morgan.paris.hilton_1_hotel-heiress-paris-hilton-rick-salomon/2?_s=PM%3ASHOWBIZ |archivedate=October 9, 2012 |df= }}</ref> In addition to a Paris Hilton Beach Club Resort in [[Manila]], [[Philippines|the Philippines]], there are currently 50 Paris Hilton stores worldwide and 19 product lines, such as handbags, watches, footwear, hair and skin care. Hilton earns over US$10&nbsp;million a year from business ventures and, as of 2015, was paid about US$300,000 for appearances in clubs and events.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2005/53/U3HH.html|title=Paris Hilton, Forbes Top Celebrities|publisher=Forbes.com|accessdate=June 19, 2013}}</ref>

==Early life==
[[File:Kathy Hilton, Paris Hilton and Kyle Richards at NBC party at TCA.jpg|thumb|upright=.91|alt=Three smiling women|Hilton with her mother [[Kathy Hilton]] and aunt [[Kyle Richards]] at an [[NBC]] party on February 5, 2011 (photo by Greg Hernandez)]]
Hilton was born in [[New York City]]. Her mother, [[Kathy Hilton]] (née Kathleen Elizabeth Avanzino),<ref>{{cite news|last=Piazza|first=Jo|title=A FIELD GUIDE TO THE HILTONS: Chronicling the history of the hideously hyped inn crowd|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/nydn-features/field-guide-hiltons-chronicling-history-hideously-hyped-inn-crowd-article-1.583788?pgno=1|accessdate=November 13, 2013|newspaper=[[NY Daily News]]|date=November 7, 2006|location=New York}}</ref><ref>''House of Hilton'' by Jerry Oppenheimer.</ref> is a socialite and former actress; her father, [[Richard Hilton|Richard Howard "Rick" Hilton]], is a businessman. Hilton is the oldest of four children; she has one sister, [[Nicky Hilton Rothschild|Nicholai Olivia "Nicky" Hilton]] (born 1983), and two brothers: Barron Nicholas Hilton II (born 1989) and Conrad Hughes Hilton III (born 1994). Her paternal great-grandfather was [[Conrad Hilton]], who founded [[Hilton Hotels & Resorts|Hilton Hotels]]. Her maternal aunts are television personalities [[Kim Richards|Kim]] and [[Kyle Richards]]. Hilton has [[Norwegian American|Norwegian]], [[German American|German]], [[Italian-American|Italian]], [[English American|English]], [[Irish American|Irish]], and [[Scottish American|Scottish]] ancestry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wargs.com/other/hilton.html|title=Ancestry of Paris Hilton|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/projo/access/31911812.html?dids=31911812:31911812&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Feb+20%2C+1997&author=&pub=The+Providence+Journal&desc=Providence+LAURENCE+K.+AVANZINO&pqatl=google|work=Providence Journal|title=Providence LAURENCE K. AVANZINO|date=February 20, 1997}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/projo/access/39692575.html?dids=39692575:39692575&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Mar+12%2C+1999&author=&pub=The+Providence+Journal&desc=Narragansett+ELIZABETH+J.+AVANZINO&pqatl=google|work=The Providence Journal|title=Narragansett ELIZABETH J. AVANZINO|date=March 12, 1999}}</ref> She was raised in the [[Catholic Church|Catholic]] faith.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news24.com/You/Archive/paris-hilton-takes-action-over-stalker-20170728|title=Paris Hilton takes action over stalker|author=|date=|website=news24.com}}</ref><ref name="Gurvis2011">{{cite book|author=Sandra Gurvis|title=Paris Hilton: A Biography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVa1lQheINwC&pg=PA26|year=2011|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-0-313-37940-6|pages=26–}}</ref>

She moved frequently in her youth, living in a suite in the [[Waldorf-Astoria Hotel]] in [[Manhattan]], [[Beverly Hills, California|Beverly Hills]] and [[the Hamptons]]. Her sister Nicky once described her as "very much a tomboy" who dreamed about becoming a veterinarian.<ref name="vice">{{cite web|url=https://broadly.vice.com/en_us/article/53nvp3/paris-hilton-profile-2015-19-fragrances-and-counting-heiress|title=This Is How Paris Hilton Fooled the Entire United States of America|date=December 9, 2015|publisher=}}</ref> As a child, she was friends with actress [[Bijou Phillips]] and socialites [[Ivanka Trump]], [[Nicole Richie]] and [[Kim Kardashian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.intouchweekly.com/posts/are-nicole-richie-and-paris-still-friends-142801|title=Are Nicole Richie and Paris Hilton Still Friends? Here's Where They Stand Today|date=September 26, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref name="vf">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/culture/2000/09/hiltons200009|title=Hip-Hop Debs! A Night (and Afternoon) with Paris and Nicky Hilton|first=Nancy Jo|last=Sales|publisher=}}</ref> Her mother was a close friend of [[Michael Jackson]], with Hilton remarking in an interview: "I grew up around Michael, and anytime he’d have a music video or a concert, he would always invite my family".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/news/features/childhood/paris-nicky-hilton-2013-4/|title=The Hilton Sisters|website=NYMag.com}}</ref>

Growing up in [[Los Angeles]], Hilton attended the [[Buckley School (California)|Buckley School]] and [[St. Paul the Apostle Church and School|St. Paul the Apostle School]], finishing elementary school in 1995.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/picturegalleries/celebritynews/8720360/School-yearbook-pictures-of-celebrities.html|location=London, UK|work=The Daily Telegraph|title=School yearbook pictures of celebrities|date=August 24, 2011}}</ref> Her freshman year of high school (1995–96) was spent at the [[Marywood-Palm Valley school|Marywood-Palm Valley School]] in [[Rancho Mirage, California]]. In 1996, Hilton and her family left California for the [[East Coast of the United States|East Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/articles/Paris-Hilton-11271420 |title=Paris Hilton Biography |publisher=A&E Television Network |work=Biography.com |year=2011 |accessdate=April 2, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903180759/http://www.biography.com/articles/Paris-Hilton-11271420 |archivedate=September 3, 2011 |df= }}</ref> At age 15, she attended [[Professional Children's School]],<ref name="vf" /> and at 16, spent one year at the [[Provo Canyon School]] for emotionally troubled teens.<ref name="Chicago Flame">{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagoflame.com/2.9141/the-real-news-1.1299436 |title=The Real News&nbsp;– Paris Hilton: I need a disguise |work=Chicago Flame |date=December 7, 2003 |accessdate=April 2, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708143717/http://www.chicagoflame.com/2.9141/the-real-news-1.1299436 |archivedate=July 8, 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name="Thiandian News">{{cite news|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/entertainment/paris-hiltons-teen-lover-threatens-to-expose-their-love-letters_1005218.html|title=Paris Hilton's teen lover threatens to expose their love letters|work=Thiandian News|date=November 15, 2007|accessdate=April 2, 2011}}</ref> She then attended the [[Dwight School]] before dropping out a few months later. "She knew no one at [Dwight]", said her mother in an interview, while a classmate described her as "sort of more sophisticated. She was different from everybody else".<ref name="vf" /> She later earned a [[General Education Development|GED]] certification.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Evonne |last=Barry |title=A million reasons to be Paris |date=December 30, 2006 |url=http://www.news.com.au/story/0,23599,20990279-5007146,00.html |work=The Daily Telegraph (Australia) |accessdate=February 1, 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070305075822/http://www.news.com.au/story/0%2C23599%2C20990279-5007146%2C00.html |archivedate=March 5, 2007 |df= }}</ref><ref name="Fox News Bio">{{Cite news|title=Paris Hilton Biography|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,195187,00.html?sPage=fnc/entertainment/celebrity/hilton|publisher=Fox News|date=June 28, 2007|accessdate=July 4, 2008}}</ref>

==Career==
===1999–2002===
After originally modeling as a child at charity events,<ref name="porter"/> Hilton signed with [[Donald Trump]]'s modeling agency, T Management, at age 19.<ref name="porter"/> She became a notable fixture in parties and social events, and her late-night persona was well-documented in local tabloids.<ref name="vice" /> A ''[[New York Post]]'' article, describing Hilton, wrote: "The most outrageous [New York City-based heiress] is hotel-darling Paris Hilton, 19, a part-time model with a tendency to flash her thong".<ref name="vice" /> Similarly, producer Cisco Adler called Hilton "a young party girl who gets sucked into the L.A. party scene and grew up a little too fast" in a ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' profile.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sales|first=Nancy Jo|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/features/2000/09/hiltons200009|title=Nancy Jo Sales on Paris and Nicky Hilton|publisher=Vanity Fair|date=March 21, 2012|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> She played an ill-fated character in the independent teen thriller ''Sweetie Pie'' (2000).<ref name="vf" />

By 2001, Hilton had developed a reputation as a socialite, and was hailed as "New York's leading [[It Girl]]", whose fame was beginning to "extend beyond the New York [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|tabloids]]".<ref name="porter">{{Cite news|last=Porter|first=Charlie|title=New York style: 'Is this article going to trash me?': Heiress, star of the social columns and now a top model.. Charlie Porter meets Paris Hilton|work=The Guardian (London)|page=Guardian Features, p. 8|date=February 16, 2001}}</ref> She made a cameo appearance as herself in the comedy ''[[Zoolander]]'', with [[Ben Stiller]], and posed for [[David LaChapelle]] in ''Vanity Fair'', alongside her sister Nicky, wearing a silver jacket with no top or bra, in September 2001.<ref name="vice" /> She also graced several other magazine covers, including the UK's ''Tatler'', Italy's ''Giola'' and the US' ''[[FHM]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Paris_Hilton|title=Paris Hilton - Fashion Model|publisher=Fashionmodeldirectory.com |accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref>

Amid her growing public profile, businessman [[George J. Maloof Jr.]] paid Hilton to wear a dress made from US$1 million in poker chips and attend the [[Palms Casino Resort]] opening in [[Las Vegas]] in November 2001,<ref name="pa">{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/paris-hilton-explains-how-she-was-paid-to-party-before-turning-21|title=Paris Hilton explains how she was paid to party before turning 21|first=Stephanie|last=Nolasco|date=November 29, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2018/01/05/paris-hilton-palms-casino-congrats-marquee-sign-gift/|title=Paris Hilton Gets Special Marquee Shout-out and Engagement Gift From Palms Casino|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lasvegassun.com/news/2001/nov/16/huge-crowd-flocks-new-resort/|title=Huge crowd flocks to new resort|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegasseven.com/2010/04/29/crazy-money/|title=‘Crazy Money’ - Vegas Seven|date=April 29, 2010|publisher=}}</ref> which was the first of numerous offers for Hilton to show up in nightclubs for promotion,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gettyimages.ca/detail/news-photo/nicky-hilton-paris-hilton-designer-lloyd-klein-and-maria-news-photo/1513596|title=Nicky Hilton, Paris Hilton, designer Lloyd Klein, and Maria Scheider...|publisher=}}</ref><ref name="pa" /> and marked the beginning of what soon became, for celebrities, making a business out of partying.<ref name="gq">{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/how-celebs-get-paid-for-club-appearances|title=How Celebs Make Big Bucks for Doing . . . Nothing|first=Carrie|last=Battan|date=April 4, 2016|publisher=}}</ref> In 2002, Hilton appeared in [[Vincent Gallo]]'s "Honey Bunny" video,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com/822728.html|title=Old Vincent Gallo Short Film Featuring Paris Hilton|publisher=Oh No They Didn't|date=December 26, 2004|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacafe.com/watch/mu-475303/honey_bunny_vincent_gallo_music_video|title=Honey Bunny-Vincent Gallo (Music Video)|publisher=Metacafe.com|date=August 9, 2011|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref> and played the lead role in the [[straight-to-DVD]] horror film ''[[Nine Lives (2002 film)|Nine Lives]]''. ''Beyondhollywood.com'', describing her role, asserted: "Hilton plays—what else?—a spoiled American socialite who shops on three continents in one day".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beyondhollywood.com/nine-lives-2002-movie-review|title=Nine Lives (2002) Movie Review|publisher=Beyondhollywood.com|accessdate=April 29, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130319041146/http://www.beyondhollywood.com/nine-lives-2002-movie-review/|archivedate=March 19, 2013}}</ref>  During the early 2000s, Hilton was a frequent model for [[Lloyd Klein]]'s fashion shows.

===2003–2007===
Hilton's breakout came in 2003, when she starred with her socialite counterpart [[Nicole Richie]] in the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] reality series ''[[The Simple Life]]'', in which they lived for a month with a family in the rural community of [[Altus, Arkansas]]. The series premiered on December 2, 2003, shortly after the release of Hilton's sex tape,<ref name="star">{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,627219,00.html|title='Simple Life' Establishes Hilton's Star|work=People|accessdate=April 6, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120227133411/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,627219,00.html|archivedate=February 27, 2012}}</ref> and was a ratings success; its first episode attracted 13 million viewers, increasing Fox's adult 18–49 rating by 79 percent.<ref>{{cite web|last=Silverman |first=Stephen M. |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,627850,00.html |title=Hilton and Richie Expand Their Horizons – The Simple Life, Nicole Richie, Paris Hilton |work=People |date=March 15, 2004 |accessdate=May 24, 2012}}</ref> The high viewership was attributed to the exposure Hilton received for the tape.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/why-paris-hilton-famous-secret-success-as-2369884.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130629092108/http://voices.yahoo.com/why-paris-hilton-famous-secret-success-as-2369884.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=June 29, 2013 |title=Why is Paris Hilton Famous? The Secret to Success as a Celebrity Heiress - Yahoo! Voices |publisher=voices.yahoo.com |date=January 1, 2009 |accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref> She became known for her onscreen [[dumb blonde]] persona—a character she eventually distanced herself from, stating she was playing a role.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-news/people/299518/paris-hilton-insists-she-s-not-stupid/1 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120913092926/http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-news/people/299518/paris-hilton-insists-she-s-not-stupid/1 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=September 13, 2012 |title=Paris Hilton insists she's not stoopid |publisher=Now magazine |accessdate=May 18, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://movieline.com/2011/01/14/paris-hilton-plays-movielines-my-favorite-scene/|title=Paris Hilton Plays My Favorite Scene: 'Who Was It? Ben Stiller or Matt Damon?'|publisher=Movieline.com|accessdate=May 18, 2012}}</ref>

The socialite introduced a [[lifestyle brand]] in 2004, helping to design a purse collection for the Japanese label [[Samantha Thavasa]]. A jewelry line designed by Hilton was sold on [[Amazon.com]] shortly after.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://msnbc.msn.com/id/5888425/|title=Paris Hilton creates jewelry line|work=TODAY.com|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,691014,00.html|title=Paris Hilton Launches Her Own Jewelry Line|publisher=People.com|accessdate=March 16, 2012}}</ref> In the fall of 2004, she released an autobiography co-written by Merle Ginsberg, ''[[Confessions of an Heiress: A Tongue-in-Chic Peek Behind the Pose]]'',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,688906,00.htm|title=Paris Dreams of Simple Life in New Book|work=People|accessdate=March 16, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120201203/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,688906,00.htm|archivedate=November 20, 2012}}</ref> with color photos and advice on life as an heiress.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,688906,00.html|title=Paris Dreams of Simple Life in New Book|work=People|accessdate=April 6, 2012}}</ref> The book was seventh on [[The New York Times Best Seller list|''The New York Times'' Best Seller list]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/26/books/bestseller/0926besthardnonfiction.html|title=Hardcover Nonfiction|work=New York Times|accessdate=April 6, 2012|date=September 26, 2004}}</ref> Her quote, "Dress cute wherever you go; life is too short to blend in", was added to [[The Oxford Dictionary of Quotations]] in September 2009.<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.reuters.com/article/artsNews/idUSTRE58A13N20090911|title=Paris Hilton's wisdom immortalized in book of quotes|publisher=Reuters|date=September 11, 2009|accessdate=September 13, 2009|first=Belinda|last=Goldsmith}}</ref> Hilton was involved in creating a perfume line by Parlux Fragrances. Originally planned for a small release, high demand led to increased availability by December 2004. Its introduction was followed by a 47-percent increase in Parlux sales, primarily of the Hilton-branded perfume.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://biz.yahoo.com/e/050815/parl10-q.html|title=Form 10-Q for Parlux Fragrances, Inc.|publisher=|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> After this success Parlux released several more perfumes with her name, including fragrances for men.<ref>[http://nowsmellthis.blogharbor.com/blog/_archives/2006/5/6/1936792.html Celebrity fragrance watch: Paris Hilton & Andy Roddick] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061026100419/http://nowsmellthis.blogharbor.com/blog/_archives/2006/5/6/1936792.html |date=October 26, 2006 }} ''Nowsmellthis.com''</ref>

[[File:Paris hilton universal photo retouched.jpg|thumb|left|upright|alt=Smiling blonde woman|Hilton at a 2005 conference in [[Munich]]]]
In February 2005, Hilton hosted [[NBC]]'s ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', with [[Keane (band)|Keane]] as the musical guest,<ref>{{cite web|last=Silverman |first=Stephen M. |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1023613,00.html |title=Paris Hilton Booked to Host SNL – Paris Hilton |work=People |date=February 2, 2005 |accessdate=May 24, 2012}}</ref> and in May, the slasher film ''[[House of Wax (2005 film)|House of Wax]]''—her first major film role—<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,627841,00.html|title=Jen, Sarah and Paris to Hit Cineplex|work=People|accessdate=April 8, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2005-03-09/entertainment/18296417_1_tribeca-film-festival-movies-star|title=Tribeca film fest lineup|work=Daily News |location=New York |accessdate=April 8, 2012|date=March 9, 2005}}</ref> was released in theaters,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teenhollywood.com/2005/04/06/paris-hilton-turns-up-the-heat-on-house-of-wax |title=Paris Hilton Turns Up The Heat On House Of Wax |publisher=TeenHollywood.com |date=April 6, 2005 |accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> to mixed reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/house-of-wax|title=House of Wax reviews|publisher=Metacritic.com|accessdate=April 8, 2012}}</ref> Writing for ''View London'', Matthew Turner remarked that Hilton "does better than you might expect",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.viewlondon.co.uk/films/house-of-wax-film-review-11774.html|title=House of Wax Film Review|last=Turner|first=Matthew|work=ViewLondon|accessdate=November 27, 2011}}</ref> while ''[[TV Guide]]'' called Hilton "talentless".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.tvguide.com/house-of-wax/review/137902|title=House of Wax Review|publisher=TV Guide|accessdate=July 27, 2012}}</ref> Her role earned her the [[Teen Choice Award]] for Best Scream and the 2005 [[Golden Raspberry Award|Razzie]] for Worst Supporting Actress.<ref name="award2">{{cite web|url=http://www.razzies.com/forum/forum_posts.asp?TID=668&PN=1|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060325080718/http://www.razzies.com/forum/forum_posts.asp?TID=668&PN=1|dead-url=yes|archive-date=March 25, 2006|title=2005 Golden Raspberry Award Nominees and Winners|publisher=|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> She also received a nomination for Best Frightened Performance at the [[2006 MTV Movie Awards]]. ''House of Wax'' grossed over US$70&nbsp;million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=houseofwax.htm|title=House of Wax (2005)|publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=June 17, 2007}}</ref> Hilton appeared in a television commercial entitled "Paris Car Wash," promoting [[Carl's Jr.]]'s Spicy Burger product, which started airing in May 2005.<ref>{{cite book |first=Margo |last=Berman |author2=Robyn Blakeman |year=2009 |chapter=Where Campaigns and Brands Go Off Course |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=vV_jXfalhtEC&lpg=PA147&dq=%22Paris%20Hilton%22%20%22that's%20hot%22%20signature&pg=PA147#v=onepage&q=%22Paris%20Hilton%22%20%22that's%20hot%22%20signature&f=false |title=The Brains Behind Great Ad Campaigns |publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield Publishers]] |location=[[Lanham, Maryland]] |page=147 |isbn=978-0-7425-5550-1 |lccn=2008055414 |accessdate=January 16, 2017 |via=Google Books }}</ref> By the fall of 2005, she had published her second book, ''[[Your Heiress Diary: Confess It All to Me]]'',<ref>{{Cite book|isbn=0743287142|title=Your Heiress Diary: Confess It All to Me|publisher=}}</ref> and introduced another fragrance, ''[[Just Me (fragrance)|Just Me]]''.

''The Simple Life'' was canceled by Fox after three seasons in 2005 following a dispute between Hilton and Richie. Neither Richie nor Hilton spoke publicly about their split, although it was speculated that they fell out after Richie showed one of Hilton's homemade sex tapes to a group of their friends.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/simple-life-star-paris-hilton-confirms-that-%22nicole-and-i-are-no-longer-friends%22-3431.php |title='Simple Life' star Paris Hilton confirms that "Nicole and I are no longer friends" |publisher=Reality TV World |date=April 21, 2005 |accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> They reconciled in October 2006.<ref>{{cite web|last=Alexander |first=Bryan |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1544365,00.html |title=Paris Hilton and Nicole Richie: Friends Again? – Nicole Richie, Paris Hilton |work=People |accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> After ''The Simple Life'' was cancelled, other networks ([[NBC]], [[The WB]], [[VH1]] and [[MTV]]) were reportedly interested in obtaining the rights for new seasons of the show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/fox-drops-the-simple-life-4-nbc-and-wb-reportedly-interested-3754.php |title=Fox drops 'The Simple Life 4,' NBC and The WB reportedly interested |publisher=Realitytvworld.com |date=October 13, 2005 |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref> On November 28, 2005, [[E!]] announced that it had picked up ''The Simple Life'', ordering the production of a fourth season and obtaining the rights to repeat the first three seasons. Shooting for the new season began on February 27, 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/fox-canceled-the-simple-life-4-reality-show-lands-at-e%21-network-1006320.php |title=Fox's canceled 'The Simple Life 4' reality show lands at E! Network |publisher=Realitytvworld.com |date=November 28, 2005 |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref> The fourth-season premiere of the show was a ratings success for its new network.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realityblurred.com/realitytv/archives/the_simple_life_4/2006_Jun_07_debut_ratings |title=Simple Life 4 debut quadruples E!'s average ratings + reality blurred |publisher=Realityblurred.com |date=June 7, 2006 |accessdate=January 30, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120908044527/http://www.realityblurred.com/realitytv/archives/the_simple_life_4/2006_Jun_07_debut_ratings |archive-date=September 8, 2012 |dead-url=yes  }}</ref>

Hilton released her self-titled debut album, ''[[Paris (Paris Hilton album)|Paris]]'', on August 22, 2006. The album reached number six on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], and sold over 600,000 copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parishiltonsite.net/music.php |title=Paris Hilton's Music |publisher=Parishiltonsite.net |accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> Its first single, "[[Stars Are Blind]]", was played on more than 125 pop stations in the U.S.<ref>{{cite web|author=UTC |url=http://www.teenmusic.com/2006/06/26/paris-hiltons-stars-are-blind-has-been-added-to-more-than-12 |title=Paris Hilton's "Stars Are Blind" Has Been Added to More Than 125 Pop Stations Nationwide |publisher=TeenMusic.com |date=June 26, 2006 |accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> The song was a worldwide hit,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teenmusic.com/2006/06/12/paris-hiltons-debut-single-is-a-hit |title=Paris Hilton's Debut Single is a Hit |publisher=TeenMusic.com |date=June 12, 2006 |accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> reaching the top ten in 17 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/fearneand/wk43ep1/default.html|title=Fearne And|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091112113017/http://www.itv.com/presscentre/fearneand/wk43ep1/default.html|archivedate=November 12, 2009}}</ref> Critical reception was generally mixed,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/paris/critic-reviews|title=Reviews for Paris|publisher=Metacritic.com|accessdate=March 16, 2012}}</ref> but ''[[AllMusic]]'' called the album "more fun than anything released by [[Britney Spears]] or [[Jessica Simpson]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=699848&aid=788893 |title=Discography – Paris Hilton – Paris CD/DVD |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090221120039/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=699848&aid=788893 |archivedate=February 21, 2009 }}</ref>

Her film ''[[Bottoms Up (2006 film)|Bottoms Up]]'' was released straight-to-DVD in late 2006. Australia's ''Urban Cinefile'', describing Hilton, wrote that she "spends most of her screen time flicking her hair as she delivers lines like 'books are those things you read.'"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.urbancinefile.com.au/home/view.asp?a=13735&s=DVD|title=BOTTOMS UP: DVD|publisher=Urban Cinefile|accessdate=April 29, 2012}}</ref>  ''[[National Lampoon's Pledge This!]]'', another film in which Hilton starred, was also released in DVD in 2006; she missed its premiere at the [[Cannes Film Festival]], protesting the addition of several nude scenes: "I was so angry I snubbed my own premiere."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/people/waving-goodbye-to-her-wiced-ways/2006/05/30/1148956336143.html|title=Too much nudity, protests Paris|accessdate=May 30, 2006|date=May 30, 2006|work=The Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref> In August 2008 Worldwide Entertainment Group sued Hilton in Miami District Court, alleging that she did not fulfill her contractual agreement to provide "reasonable promotion and publicity" for the film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/2008-08-12-2294854685_x.htm|title=Paris Hilton sued over lack of publicity for film|date=August 13, 2008|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=April 3, 2014}}</ref> She reportedly received US$1&nbsp;million for her role. Also in 2006, Hilton licensed her name to Gameloft for their mobile video game ''Paris Hilton's Diamond Quest''.

[[File:Hilton, Paris (2007).jpg|thumb|upright|alt=Smiling blonde woman at an awards ceremony|Hilton at the 2007 [[Scream Awards]]]]
On January 10, 2007, Hilton introduced her DreamCatchers line of hair extensions in partnership with Hair Tech International.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreamcatchers.com/ParisHilton_AboutUs.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070410090221/http://www.dreamcatchers.com/ParisHilton_AboutUs.html|archivedate=April 10, 2007|title=DreamCatchers by Paris Hilton|publisher=Web.archive.org|date=April 10, 2007|accessdate=April 3, 2014}}</ref> Due to her incarceration, ''The Simple Life'' finished its run at the end of its fifth season in July 2007. In early August, Hilton signed a licensing agreement with Antebi for a signature footwear line (Paris Hilton Footwear, featuring stilettos, platforms, flats, wedges and a sports collection) which reached stores in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-6807815/Paris-Hilton-Inks-Deal-with.html|title=Paris Hilton Inks Deal with Antebi Footwear Group|work=Manta|accessdate=September 17, 2014}}</ref> In mid-August, she introduced a line of tops, dresses, coats and jeans at the [[Kitson Boutique]] in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/20305192|title=Hilton's clothing launch sparks L.A. frenzy|work=TODAY.com|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>  In December 2007, she posed nude (covered with gold paint) to promote "Rich [[Prosecco]]", a canned version of the [[Italian wine|Italian]] sparkling wine,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvshark.com/read/?art=arc1232|title=Paris Hilton Nude, Naked In Gold For Canned Champagne Ad – Rich Prosecco Wine|publisher=|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Stuff.co.nz_175817">{{cite news |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/175817 |title=Nude Paris launches 'wine in a can' (+photo) |work=[[Stuff.co.nz]] |accessdate=November 1, 2011}}</ref> traveling to Germany to appear in print ads for the wine.<ref>{{Cite news
|url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,316541,00.html |title = Paris Hilton Wears Nothing but Gold Paint for Champagne Ad |accessdate = December 31, 2007 |date=December 12, 2007 |work=[[Fox News]]}}</ref> In 2007, Hilton also modeled for 2 B Free<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imnotobsessed.com/2007/03/20/paris-hilton-strutted-her-stuff-on-the-2-b-free-runway/ |title=Paris Hilton Strutted Her Stuff On The 2 B Free Runway |work=Celeb Gossip, Celeb News and Celeb Pictures by I'm Not Obsessed |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905195635/http://www.imnotobsessed.com/2007/03/20/paris-hilton-strutted-her-stuff-on-the-2-b-free-runway/ |archivedate=September 5, 2014 |df= }}</ref> and introduced her fourth perfume, [[Can Can (fragrance)|Can Can]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.celebrity-mania.com/news/view/00002863.html |title=Paris Hilton's New Business Venture: Shoes |publisher=Celebrity-mania.com |date=August 1, 2007 |accessdate=September 5, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923201610/http://www.celebrity-mania.com/news/view/00002863.html |archivedate=September 23, 2015  }}</ref>

===2008–2011===
In February 2008, ''[[The Hottie and the Nottie]]'', a romantic comedy in which Hilton starred, was released theatrically;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=hottieandthenottie.htm|title=The Hottie & the Nottie (2008) - Box Office Mojo|website=Boxofficemojo.com|accessdate=September 30, 2017}}</ref> the film was a critical and commercial failure,<ref>{{cite news|title=The 100 Worst Movies of 2008|url=http://entertainment.timesonline.co.uk/tol/arts_and_entertainment/film/article5245052.ece|work=The Times|date=October 23, 2007|accessdate=January 3, 2009|location=London}}</ref> with Hilton eventually receiving the [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Actress]]. Hilton's love for dogs led her to create a canine apparel line, Little Lily by Paris Hilton, with some of the proceeds benefiting animal rescue, in early 2008.<ref>Gould, Mignon A. [http://www.mignongould.com/paris-talks-togs.pdf Paris Talks Togs — People's and Pet's] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090326111239/http://www.mignongould.com/paris-talks-togs.pdf |date=March 26, 2009 }}. 'Yes Magazine/The Arizona Republic'. February 8, 2008.</ref> In April 2008, she appeared in the ''[[My Name Is Earl]]'' episode "[[Creative Writing (My Name Is Earl)|I Won't Die with a Little Help from My Friends]]".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tv.com/story/10960.html |title=Cast updates: Her Name is Paris |first=Tim |last=Surette |work=TV.com |date=April 3, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080306070811/http://www.tv.com/story/10960.html |archivedate=March 6, 2008 |df= }}</ref>

On August 6, 2008 Hilton appeared in an online video, ''Paris Hilton Responds to McCain Ad'', directed by [[Adam McKay]] and posted on the [[Funny or Die]] website.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/politics/2008/08/paris-hilton-re/|title=Paris Hilton Responds to McCain Celeb Commercial|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=July 27, 2012}}</ref> The video, featuring Hilton in a [[parody advertisement]], was made in response to a television [[Campaign advertising|campaign ad]] ("Celeb") by the [[John McCain presidential campaign, 2008|2008 John McCain presidential campaign]].<ref name="phspoof">{{cite news|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1592229/paris-hilton-responds-mccain-ad-with-her-own-clip.jhtml|title=Paris Hilton Responds To John McCain Ad With Her Own Campaign Video|publisher=''MTV''|accessdate=July 17, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20217116,00.html|title=VIDEO: Paris Hilton Responds to McCain Ad|work=People|accessdate=July 27, 2012}}</ref> In "Celeb" McCain compared [[Barack Obama]] to celebrities such as Hilton and [[Britney Spears]], questioning his readiness to lead and criticizing his energy policy.<ref name="phspoof" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20216117,00.html|title=Paris Hilton's Cold Reaction to John McCain Commercial|work=People|accessdate=July 27, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.cnn.com/2008-07-30/politics/mccain.ad_1_new-campaign-ad-barack-obama-mccain-campaign?_s=PM:POLITICS |title=McCain ad compares Obama to Britney Spears, Paris Hilton |publisher=CNN |accessdate=July 17, 2012 |date=July 25, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120129084802/http://articles.cnn.com/2008-07-30/politics/mccain.ad_1_new-campaign-ad-barack-obama-mccain-campaign?_s=PM%3APOLITICS |archivedate=January 29, 2012 |df= }}</ref> In what ''[[The Washington Post]]'' said "might just be her best acting role yet",<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/08/06/AR2008080601084.html|title=Paris for Prez?|first=Jose Antonio|last=Vargas|work=Washington Post|date=August 6, 2008|accessdate=May 2, 2012}}</ref> Hilton wore a leopard-print swimsuit in the video.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jay|last=Fitzgerald|title=Paris Hilton electrifies campaign|url=http://www.bostonherald.com/news/national/politics/2008/view.bg?articleid=1111580&srvc=rss|publisher=Boston Herald |date=August 7, 2008|accessdate=August 20, 2008}}</ref> It had seven million views in two days, receiving worldwide press coverage and written and verbal responses from both campaigns.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/paris-for-president-ndash-and-shes-gunning-for-mccain-887111.html|title=Paris for President – and she's gunning for McCain|work=The Independent|accessdate=July 27, 2012|location=London|first=Rupert|last=Cornwell|date=August 7, 2008}}</ref>

At the [[2008 Toronto International Film Festival]] a documentary about Hilton, ''[[Paris, Not France]]'', was screened.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2008/09/10/us-toronto-hilton-idINN1040315820080910|title=Paris Hilton lights up Toronto film festival|agency=Reuters|accessdate=May 19, 2012|date=September 10, 2008}}</ref> She starred in a MTV reality series, ''[[Paris Hilton's My New BFF]]'', about her search for a new best friend,<ref>{{Cite news|first=Dave|last=West|title=Hilton will seek best friend in new show|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/ustv/a91546/hilton-will-seek-best-friend-in-new-show.html|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|date=March 14, 2008|accessdate=March 15, 2008}}</ref> which premiered shortly after, on September 30, 2008.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Hilton searching for new best friend|url=http://www.rte.ie/arts/2008/0314/hiltonp.html|publisher=[[RTÉ]]|date=March 14, 2008|accessdate=March 17, 2008}}</ref> The series was a hit and topped all other cable shows in its time slot.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fitzgerald |first=Toni |url=http://www.medialifemagazine.com/artman2/publish/Cable_20/So-hot_Paris_and_hot_all_over_again.asp |title=So-hot Paris, and hot all over again |publisher=Media Life Magazine |date=October 22, 2008 |accessdate=May 24, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081227120419/http://www.medialifemagazine.com/artman2/publish/Cable_20/So-hot_Paris_and_hot_all_over_again.asp |archivedate=December 27, 2008 |df= }}</ref> In October, she appeared in a second parody video on ''[[Funny or Die]]'', "Paris Hilton Gets Presidential with Martin Sheen", with [[Martin Sheen]]; Sheen's son, actor [[Charlie Sheen]], made a cameo appearance.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20231900,00.html|title=VIDEO: Paris Hilton Gets (Fake) Presidential Advice – From Martin Sheen|work=People|accessdate=July 27, 2012}}</ref> Hilton, in a green evening dress and wearing heavy makeup, discusses political issues with [[Martin Sheen]] in his ''[[The West Wing|West Wing]]'' role.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Paris Hilton is joined by Martin Sheen for her fake US presidential campaign|work=The Times |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/us_and_americas/article4910791.ece|first=Sophie|last=Tedmanson|date=October 9, 2008|location=London}}</ref>

In her next film, the [[Gothic rock]] musical ''[[Repo! The Genetic Opera]]'',<ref>{{cite web|last=Nudd|first=Tim|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20048817,00.html|title=Paris Hilton Singing a New Tune: Opera|work=People|date=July 30, 2007|accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> she played Amber Sweet, the surgery and painkiller-addicted daughter of a biotech magnate. After screening  at the 2008 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]], the film received a [[limited release]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/films.php?id=22928|title=Repo! The Genetic Opera Trailer, News, Videos, and Reviews|publisher=ComingSoon.net|accessdate=April 3, 2014}}</ref> ''Horror.com'' said: "Not only is this by far Hilton's best role, she's actually got a grain of gravitas in the end".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.horror.com/php/article-1909-1.html |title=Repo! The Genetic Opera |publisher=Horror.com |accessdate=May 10, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213230443/http://www.horror.com/php/article-1909-1.html |archivedate=February 13, 2012 |df= }}</ref> However, ''Jam! Movies'' called her a "hopeless twit as an actress".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Reviews/R/Repo_The_Genetic_Opera/2008/11/2|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130115092142/http://jam.canoe.ca/Movies/Reviews/R/Repo_The_Genetic_Opera/2008/11/2|deadurl=yes|title=CANOE - Canadian Online Explorer - Canada's news, sports, entertainme…|date=January 15, 2013|archivedate=January 15, 2013|publisher=}}</ref> She was nominated for the 2009 [[Razzie Award for Worst Supporting Actress]] for the role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/2009-razzi-award-nominees-2654011.html |title=2009 Razzi Award Nominees |publisher=voices.yahoo.com |date=February 20, 2009 |accessdate=August 10, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140619195823/http://voices.yahoo.com/2009-razzi-award-nominees-2654011.html |archivedate=June 19, 2014 |df= }}</ref> Around that time, Hilton released her fifth fragrance for women, Fairy Dust.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clevelandleader.com/node/8002 |title=Fairy Dust by Paris Hilton Fragrance |publisher=Clevelandleader.com |accessdate=May 19, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121123114628/http://www.clevelandleader.com/node/8002 |archivedate=November 23, 2012 |df= }}</ref>

[[File:Paris Hilton Tiff 09.jpg|thumb|upright|left|alt=Smiling blonde woman|Hilton at the [[2008 Toronto International Film Festival]]]]
As a result of the American version's success, on January 29, 2009 ''[[Paris Hilton's British Best Friend]]'' debuted on ITV2 in England.<ref>{{cite news|author=Leigh Holmwood |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2008/aug/20/itv.television |title=Paris Hilton's first UK show leads ITV2 autumn lineup|work=The Guardian |accessdate=September 5, 2012 |location=London |date=August 20, 2008}}</ref> The second season of ''[[Paris Hilton's My New BFF (season 2)|Paris Hilton's My New BFF]]'' premiered on June 2, 2009. Hilton shot at the time ''[[Paris Hilton's Dubai BFF]]'',<ref>{{Cite news| url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118004397.html?categoryid=19&cs=1|title=Paris Hilton pursues Mideast 'BFF'|first=Michael|last=Schneider|work=Variety|date=June 1, 2009}}</ref> which was finally broadcast in 2011. In May 2009, Hilton won the Female Celebrity Fragrance of the Year Award at the 2009 [[Fifi Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/fragrance/the-2009-fifi-awards-2145833?full=true|title=The 2009 FiFi Awards Winners Announced|publisher=WWD.com|date=May 27, 2009|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metrolyrics.com/2009-paris-hilton-has-won-the-best-celebrity-fragrance-at-the-fragrance-foundation-fifi-awards-news.html|title=Paris Hilton Has Won The Best Celebrity Fragrance At The Fragrance Foundation FIFI Awards|publisher=Metrolyrics.com|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> in July, her sixth fragrance for women, [[Siren (fragrance)|Siren]], was introduced,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/2301954_Paris_Hilton_To_Launch_Siren_Scent |title=Paris Hilton To Launch "Siren" Scent |publisher=The Insider |accessdate=August 25, 2009 }}{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=BabbaQ |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and in August, she appeared in the fifth episode of ''[[Supernatural (U.S. TV series)|Supernatural]]''{{'}}s fifth season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/137862/paris-hilton-to-guest-star-on-cw-s-supernatural |title=Paris Hilton To Guest Star On Cws Supernatural |publisher=E! Online |date=August 5, 2009 |accessdate=December 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| author=Joyce Eng|title=Paris Hilton to Haunt Supernatural|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Paris-Hilton-Guest-1008773.aspx|work=TVGuide.com|date=August 7, 2009|accessdate=August 7, 2009}}</ref> She was involved in the creation of a sunglass line by Gripping Eyewear, which she introduced in October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2009/oct/02/paris-hilton-promos-new-sunglasses-line-las-vegas-|title=Paris Hilton promos sunglasses line in Las Vegas|publisher=Lasvegassun.com|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> In November, Hilton introduced a hair-and-beauty-products line which included shampoos, conditioners and hair vitamins.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crushable.com/2009/11/19/entertainment/paris-hilton-talks-her-new-beauty-and-hair-line/#ixzz2ElLqKxA8|title=Paris Hilton Talks Her New Beauty and Hair Line|publisher=Crushable|date=November 19, 2009|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref>

In February 2010, Hilton participated in an advertising campaign for the Brazilian beer [[Primo Schincariol|Devassa Bem Loura]], whose slogan roughly translates into English as "very blonde bitch".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oglobo.globo.com/economia/mat/2010/02/10/schincariol-anuncia-paris-hilton-como-garota-propaganda-da-nova-cerveja-devassa-915829912.asp|title=Schincariol anuncia Paris Hilton como garota propaganda da nova cerveja Devassa|date=February 10, 2010|work=O Globo|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> As part of the campaign, she rode the brewery's float in the [[Rio Carnival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://carnaval.ig.com.br/noticias/riodejaneiro/2010/02/10/pela+primeira+vez+no+carnaval+do+rio+paris+hilton+deve+comemorar+o+aniversario+na+cidade+9393492.html|title=Pela primeira vez no carnaval do Rio, Paris Hilton deve comemorar o aniversário na cidade|work=Carnaval|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> On August 10, Hilton released her 10th fragrance, Tease, which was inspired by [[Marilyn Monroe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://main.stylelist.com/2010/08/11/paris-hilton-tease-perfume/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120214102730/http://main.stylelist.com/2010/08/11/paris-hilton-tease-perfume/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=February 14, 2012|title=Paris Hilton 'Tease' Perfume Launch an Ode to Marilyn Monroe – StyleList|work=Stylelist|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> On August 19, she launched a footwear line in Las Vegas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2010/08/19/paris-hilton-launches-shoe-collection-484459/ |title=Paris Hilton launches shoe collection &#124; Metro News |publisher=Metro.co.uk |date=August 19, 2010 |accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> The critically acclaimed documentary ''[[Teenage Paparazzo]]'', in which Hilton appeared, aired on [[HBO]] on September 27.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/teenage-paparazzi|title=Teenage Paparazzo|publisher=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref>

She had her first voice-over role in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] made-for-television film ''[[The Dog Who Saved Christmas Vacation]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Mario-Lopez-Interview-1026130.aspx |title=Mario Lopez Shares 5 Reasons to Watch The Dog Who Saved Christmas Vacation – Today's News: Our Take |publisher=TVGuide.com |date=November 27, 2010 |accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref><ref name="abcfilm">{{Cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/paris_hilton_going_dogs_this_christmas/210788|title=Paris Hilton Going to the Dogs This Christmas|work= E! Online|accessdate= November 27, 2011}}</ref> The film aired on November 28, 2010<ref name="abcfilm" /> and received good ratings, with 2.611&nbsp;million viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/11/30/sunday-cable-ratings-boardwalk-empiredips-soul-train-awards-real-housewives-dexter-top-gear-more/73858/|title=Sunday Cable Ratings: Boardwalk Empire Dips; Soul Train Awards, Real Housewives, Dexter, Top Gear & More|publisher=By the numbers|accessdate=April 26, 2012}}</ref> In December 2010, Hilton launched her motorcycle team;<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-31749_162-20026222-10391698.html |title=Paris Hilton Launches Own Motorcycle Racing Team |publisher=Cbsnews.com |accessdate=April 26, 2012 |deadurl=yes |date=December 20, 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120410145937/http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-31749_162-20026222-10391698.html |archivedate=April 10, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popeater.com/2010/12/20/paris-hilton-motorcyle-supermartxe-vip/|title=Paris Hilton Launches Motorcycle Racing Team|author=AOL|work=PopEater|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> her Spanish driver, [[Maverick Viñales]], won the final race and finished third overall in the 125cc world championship the following November.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/201111076495/paris-hilton-motogp-team-wins|title=Paris Hilton expands her empire with her own winning MotoGP racing team|work=Hello!|date=November 7, 2011|accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> She modeled for a second time at the 2011 Brazil Fashion Week (her first time was in early 2010). In February, Hilton introduced a fragrance line, the Passport Collection, with perfumes inspired by cities such as [[Paris]], [[South Beach, Florida]] and [[Tokyo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nstperfume.com/2011/01/24/paris-hilton-passport-tokyo-paris-and-south-beach-new-fragrances/|title=Paris Hilton Passport Tokyo, Paris and South Beach ~ new fragrances :: Now Smell This|author=Robin|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> The following month, she introduced a footwear collection in Mexico.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/money/media/2011-03-30-paris-hilton-shoes-career.htm|title=Paris Hilton talks shoes, career: 'There is nothing else to do'|publisher=Usatoday30.usatoday.com|date=March 30, 2011|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/photos/-mtv-style-hot-shoes-2011-edition/1656346/5991082/photo.jhtml |title=Paris Hilton at the launch of her new line of shoes 'Paris Hilton The Shoe Collection' in Mexico City |publisher=Mtv.com |accessdate=January 30, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526031605/http://www.mtv.com/photos/-mtv-style-hot-shoes-2011-edition/1656346/5991082/photo.jhtml |archivedate=May 26, 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/233623/paris-hilton-pimps-new-shoe-line-and-takes-potshots-at-kim-kardashian|title=Paris Hilton Pimps New Shoe Line...and Takes Potshots at Kim Kardashian!|publisher=E! Online|date=March 30, 2011|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> Around that time, she introduced a mobile application which became available for iPhone and iPod touch.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.extratv.com/2011/02/21/get-the-new-paris-hilton-app|title=Get the New Paris Hilton App!|publisher=ExtraTV.com|date=February 21, 2011|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref>

On May 12, 2011, Hilton opened her third store in [[the Philippines]], at the Abreeza Mall in Davao City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/05/21/11/paris-hilton-shop-opens-davao|title=Paris Hilton shop opens in Davao|publisher=ABS-CBN News|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref> On June 1, she returned to reality television in [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]]'s ''[[The World According to Paris]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/pagesix/walters_grilling_burns_paris_SQ3XjJMLlpNyfW9kGWELYO |title=Paris Hilton's TV comeback unplugged after disastrous appearance on "The View" |publisher=NYPOST.com |date=June 4, 2011 |accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> The show, which followed her daily life,<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSTRE6905L920101001|work=Reuters|first=Jill|last=Serjeant|title=Paris Hilton to show her real life in new TV show|date=October 1, 2010}}</ref> was not a success,<ref>{{cite news |author=Canada |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/arts/video/video-paris-hilton-defends-reality-show-bomb/article2051615/ |title=Video: Paris Hilton defends reality show bomb |work=Globe and Mail |date=June 8, 2011 |accessdate=May 24, 2012 |location=Toronto |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612141556/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/arts/video/video-paris-hilton-defends-reality-show-bomb/article2051615/ |archivedate=June 12, 2011  }}</ref> which led to a belief that Hilton's popularity was fading.<ref>{{cite web|last=Raymond |first=Kitty |url=http://www.sfexaminer.com/entertainment/scoop/2011/06/paris-hilton-s-star-appears-be-fading |title=Paris Hilton's star appears to be fading &#124; Kitty Raymond &#124; Scoop! &#124; San Francisco Examiner |publisher=Sfexaminer.com |accessdate=December 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121125025347/http://www.sfexaminer.com/entertainment/scoop/2011/06/paris-hilton-s-star-appears-be-fading |archivedate=November 25, 2012 |df= }}</ref> ''[[The New York Times]]'' wrote that she "is an attractive woman with proven talent for marketing and self-promotion, though as a reality heroine she seems a little passé [...] it's hard to see how she can recapture the kind of audience she enjoyed in her heyday—even by streaming her premiere live on Facebook".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tv.nytimes.com/2011/06/01/arts/television/paris-hilton-in-the-world-according-to-paris.html|title=In a Bentley, Trying to Catch the Spotlight Again|work=The New York Times|accessdate=May 10, 2012|first=Alessandra|last=Stanley|date=May 31, 2011}}</ref> Nevertheless, she was labeled a "Billion Dollar Entrepreneur" by ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' magazine, and was featured on its cover.<ref>[http://www.parishilton.com/2011/06/billion-dollar-entrepreneur.html Variety: Paris Hilton – Billion Dollar Entrepreneur]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110802203203/http://www.parishilton.com/2011/06/billion-dollar-entrepreneur.html |date=August 2, 2011 }}, ParisHilton.com, June 28, 2011; retrieved October 28, 2011.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/paris-hilton-celebutante-billion-dollar-mogul/story?id=14112550|title=Paris Hilton: From Celebutante to Billion Dollar Mogul|publisher=ABC News|date=July 20, 2011|accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> Hilton opened her fourth store in the [[Philippines]] on August 18, 2011.<ref>[http://www.parishilton.com/2011/05/paris-hilton-opening-3rd-store-in-the-philippines.html Opening 3rd Store In The Philippines] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903024648/http://www.parishilton.com/2011/05/paris-hilton-opening-3rd-store-in-the-philippines.html |date=September 3, 2011 }}. Paris Hilton (May 9, 2011). Retrieved on October 28, 2011.</ref><ref name="ph.news.yahoo.com">{{cite news|agency=Associated Press|url=http://ph.news.yahoo.com/paris-hilton-opens-handbag-store-manila-131113639.html|title=Paris Hilton opens new handbag store in Manila|work=Yahoo! News Philippines|date=August 18, 2011|accessdate=June 16, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140905195017/https://ph.news.yahoo.com/paris-hilton-opens-handbag-store-manila-131113639.html|archivedate=September 5, 2014}}</ref><ref name="ph.news.yahoo.com"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/lifestyle/08/16/11/paris-hilton-meet-greet-fans-manila|title=Paris Hilton to open 4th boutique in the Philippines|publisher=ABS-CBN News|accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref> In September, she introduced a footwear line in [[Istanbul]],<ref>{{cite web|author=JustLuxe|url=http://shine.yahoo.com/work-money/paris-hilton-launches-her-shoe-line-in-istanbul-2570127.html|title=Paris Hilton Launches Her Shoe Line in Istanbul|publisher=Shine.yahoo.com|date=September 27, 2011|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celebdirtylaundry.com/2011/paris-hilton-gives-press-conference-in-istanbul-explains-that-business-runs-in-my-blood|title=Paris Hilton Gives Press Conference In Istanbul - Explains That Business 'Runs In My Blood'|publisher=Celeb Dirty Laundry |date=September 23, 2011|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref> and a Paris Hilton store opened in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radaronline.com/exclusives/2011/09/paris-hilton-opens-luxury-store-india|title=Paris Hilton Opens Luxury Store In India|date=September 26, 2011|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> Hilton modeled for designer Andre Tan during Ukraine Fashion Week in October 2011.

===2012–present===
[[File:Paris Hilton 2012.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Hilton in [[Australia]], during a 2012 visit]]
In February 2012, Hilton introduced a new line of sunglasses in Shanghai,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebs.gather.com/viewArticle.action?articleId=281474981132379 |title=Paris Hilton Launches Stylish Sunglass Line in... |publisher=Celebs.gather.com |accessdate=May 24, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120720141007/http://celebs.gather.com/viewArticle.action?articleId=281474981132379 |archivedate=July 20, 2012 |df= }}</ref> which she called a "huge success",<ref name="philtonbrand">{{cite news|url=http://www.papermag.com/2012/03/kathy_ad_paris_hilton_chat_wi.php|title=Paris Hilton + Kathy Hilton Chat With Us About Clothes and Going to Taco Bell|publisher=[[Papermag.com]]|accessdate=March 19, 2012}}</ref> and in May, she released her fifteenth perfume, Dazzle.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2012-05-25/news/31854158_1_perfume-hot-ticket-boutiques|title=Paris Hilton has sold $1.5 billion worth of perfume; 'Dazzle' will be her fifteenth fragrance |publisher=Articles.nydailynews.com|accessdate=June 16, 2013 |location=New York}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/celebrity/news/a383710/paris-hilton-to-launch-15th-fragrance-dazzle-this-summer.html|title=Paris Hilton to launch 15th fragrance Dazzle this summer|publisher=Digital Spy|date=May 25, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/05/25/paris-hilton-perfume-dazzle-fragrance_n_1545083.html|title=Paris Hilton Perfume Empire Gets New Fragrance, 'Dazzle'|publisher=Huffingtonpost.com|date=May 25, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013|first=Ellie|last=Krupnick}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.celebdirtylaundry.com/2012/paris-hilton-dazzle-perfume|title=Dazzle Perfume|publisher=Celeb Dirty Laundry|date=May 27, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref> In June, Hilton made her debut as a DJ at a Brazilian pop-music festival,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/488506/paris-hilton-to-make-dj-debut-at-pop-music-festival|title=Paris Hilton to Make DJ Debut at Pop Music Festival|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 19, 2012}}</ref> attracting a great deal of controversy and negative responses from DJs [[Deadmau5]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://perezhilton.com/2012-06-28-deadmau5-hates-paris-hilton-tweets-video|title=Deadmau5 Calls Paris Hilton's DJing Apocalyptic!|publisher=PerezHilton.com|date=June 28, 2012|accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> [[Samantha Ronson]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Zach|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/samantha-ronson-slams-paris-hiltons-new-dj-career-2012107|title=Samantha Ronson Slams Paris Hilton's New DJ Career|publisher=UsMagazine.com|date=July 10, 2012|accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> and Afrojack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com/70064373.html |title=Oh No They Didn't! – Afrojack Comments on BPM about Paris Hilton's DJ Skills..NOT GOOD |publisher=Ohnotheydidnt.livejournal.com |date=June 29, 2012 |accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> Shortly after her performance, she became a trending topic on Twitter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/showbiz/news/a389447/paris-hilton-makes-dj-debut-in-brazil-video.html|title=Paris Hilton makes DJ debut in Brazil|publisher=Digital Spy|date=June 25, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref>

In August 2012, her footwear line was nominated for the Best Celebrity Licensee of the Year award at the International Licensing Excellence Awards,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/paris-hilton-shoe-line-up-for-fashion-award_1344381|title=Paris Hilton Shoe Line Up For Fashion Award|publisher=Contactmusic|accessdate=August 10, 2012}}</ref> and the socialite appeared in a music video for Korean singer [[Kim Jang-hoon]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Paris Hilton Is Going K-Pop!|url=http://perezhilton.com/2012-08-23-paris-hilton-to-star-in-3d-k-pop-music-video|publisher=PerezHilton.com|accessdate=September 8, 2012|date=August 23, 2012}}</ref> which was filmed on [[Malibu, California|Malibu Beach]]. She was reportedly paid US$1&nbsp;million for her appearance in the video,<ref>{{cite web|title=Paris Hilton – Paris Hilton Paid 1M For Korean Pop Video|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/paris-hilton-paid-1m-for-korean-pop-video_1407065|publisher=contactmusic.com|accessdate=September 8, 2012|date=August 31, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a402986/paris-hilton-paid-usd1-million-for-korean-pop-video-appearance.html|title=Paris Hilton paid $1 million for Korean pop video appearance|publisher=Digital Spy|date=August 31, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref> which premiered in 3D in October 2012.<ref>{{cite news|last=Smart|first=Gordon|title=Paris Hilton's appeal still burns strong – in Korea|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/4513738/Paris-Hilton-earns-1million-for-two-day-job-wearing-swimsuit-in-Korean-music-video.html|work=Showbiz|accessdate=September 8, 2012|date=August 31, 2012|location=London}}</ref> In November, Hilton opened a store in [[Mecca]]; since it is considered the "holiest city in the Muslim world" and Saudi Arabia is a conservative country, controversy about her personal life swirled on [[Twitter]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/11/20/world/meast/paris-hilton-store-mecca|title=Paris Hilton whips up a storm in holy Mecca|publisher=Edition.cnn.com|accessdate=December 1, 2012|date=November 22, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.ie/lifestyle/independent-woman/fashion/paris-hilton-upsets-islamic-community-by-opening-handbag-shop-in-mecca-3300906.html|title=Paris Hilton upsets Islamic community by opening handbag shop in Mecca|publisher=Independent.ie|accessdate=December 1, 2012|date=December 3, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfexaminer.com/entertainment/scoop/2012/11/paris-hilton-mecca-not-holy-pilgrimage |title=Paris Hilton in Mecca but not for a holy pilgrimage |publisher=Sfexaminer.com |accessdate=December 1, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121127180226/http://www.sfexaminer.com/entertainment/scoop/2012/11/paris-hilton-mecca-not-holy-pilgrimage |archivedate=November 27, 2012 |df= }}</ref> In early December, she modeled for designers Shane and Falguni Peacock at [[India Fashion Week]],<ref>{{cite web|author=ApunKaChoice |url=http://www.apunkachoice.com/content/slide_show/sid100012509-pics_paris_hilton_walks_the_ramp_at_india_resort_fashion_week |title=Pics: Paris Hilton walks the ramp at India Resort Fashion Week |publisher=ApunKaChoice.com |date=December 3, 2012 |accessdate=June 19, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603154838/http://www.apunkachoice.com/content/slide_show/sid100012509-pics_paris_hilton_walks_the_ramp_at_india_resort_fashion_week/ |archivedate=June 3, 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/indian-fashion-is-stylish-and-elegant-paris-hilton/1039043|title=Indian fashion is stylish and elegant: Paris Hilton|publisher=Indian Express|date=December 1, 2012|accessdate=June 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-05/bollywood/35595366_1_paris-hilton-bollywood-celebs-riddhi-siddhi|title=Paris Hilton, Bollywood celebs at fashion week in Goa - Times Of India|publisher=Articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com|date=November 29, 2012|accessdate=June 19, 2013}}</ref> also appearing as a DJ.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.samaylive.com/entertainment-news/676519057/paris-hilton-to-dj-in-goa-for-india-resort-fashion-week-on-saturday.html|title=Paris Hilton to DJ in Goa for India Resort Fashion Week on Saturday|publisher=English.samaylive.com|date=December 1, 2012|accessdate=June 19, 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726021610/http://english.samaylive.com/entertainment-news/676519057/paris-hilton-to-dj-in-goa-for-india-resort-fashion-week-on-saturday.html|archivedate=July 26, 2013}}</ref>

In January 2013, Hilton appeared in four episodes of the Danish version of ''[[Paradise Hotel]]'', for which she was reportedly paid $300,000,{{cn|date=November 2018}} and also appeared in two episodes of ''[[The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills]]'', in which her aunts [[Kyle Richards|Kyle]] and [[Kim Richards]] star.<ref>{{cite news|last=McEwen |first=Lauren |date=January 22, 2013 |title='Real Housewives of Beverly Hills' recap, Paris Hilton and other ghosts |url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2013-01-22/entertainment/bal-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-recap-paris-hilton-and-other-ghosts-20130122_1_brandi-yolanda-kyle-and-mauricio |newspaper=[[The Baltimore Sun]] |access-date=January 14, 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120135058/http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2013-01-22/entertainment/bal-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills-recap-paris-hilton-and-other-ghosts-20130122_1_brandi-yolanda-kyle-and-mauricio |archivedate=January 20, 2016 |df= }}</ref> In April, Hilton opened the 44th Paris Hilton store in [[Bogotá, Colombia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/entertainment/2013/04/30/paris-hilton-and-her-handbags-adored-in-colombia|title=Paris Hilton, And Her Handbags, Adored In Colombia|publisher=[[Fox News Channel|Fox News Latino]]|date=April 30, 2013|accessdate=June 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Capo|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/04/25/paris-hilton-colombia-spoiled_n_3156670.html|title=Paris Hilton Opens New Store In Colombia, Assures She Is Not A Spoiled Brat|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=June 19, 2013|date=April 25, 2013}}</ref> In May, Hilton signed with [[Cash Money Records]] and appeared in the music video for [[Cash Money Records|Rich Gang]]'s song "[[Tapout (song)|Tapout]]", alongside [[Lil Wayne]], [[Christina Milian]] and [[Nicki Minaj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a466102/paris-hilton-shoots-music-video-with-nicki-minaj-lil-wayne.html|title=Paris Hilton shoots music video with Nicki Minaj, Lil Wayne|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|date=March 15, 2013|accessdate=June 19, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Paris Hilton to Release Second Album on Cash Money, Feature Lil Wayne|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/1563170/paris-hilton-to-release-second-album-on-cash-money-feature-lil|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 23, 2013|date=May 22, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|title=Paris Hilton Joins Lil Wayne's Cash Money Family?|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1707867/paris-hilton-signs-to-cash-money-lil-wayne.jhtml|work=MTV|accessdate=May 23, 2013|date=May 22, 2013}}</ref>

Hilton made a cameo appearance in [[Sofia Coppola]]'s film ''[[The Bling Ring]]'' (2013), about the infamous group of teenagers who had robbed homes of celebrities such as Hilton, [[Lindsay Lohan]] and [[Orlando Bloom]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a373935/paris-hilton-to-cameo-as-herself-in-emma-watsons-the-bling-ring.html|title=Paris Hilton 'to cameo as herself in Emma Watson's The Bling Ring'|publisher=Digital Spy|date=March 29, 2012|accessdate=September 5, 2012}}</ref> In addition to appearing in the film, she loaned Coppola her house for two weeks of shooting.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/people/2013/06/14/paris-hilton-bling-ring/2415747|title=Coppola: Filming in Paris Hilton's house was 'wild'|publisher=Usatoday.com|date=June 14, 2013|accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bling-ring-paris-hilton-tells-569203|title='Bling Ring': Paris Hilton Tells Cast, 'Don't Burn My House Down'|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=June 14, 2013|accessdate=September 2, 2013|first=Sophie|last=Schillaci}}</ref> Recalling the house, Coppola said: "It was like we have to get this into the movie. It was so unique. It would be hard to recreate that. She is larger than life and her house is like Paris World."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2013/05/cannes-paris-hilton-cried-watching-bling-ring.html|title=Cannes: Paris Hilton Cried While Watching ''The Bling Ring''|date=May 17, 2013|first=Kyle|last=Buchanan|work=Vulture.com|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref>

[[File:Paris Hilton Cannes 2016 4.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Hilton at the [[2016 Cannes Film Festival]]]]
During August 2013, Hilton was a DJ at [[Amnesia (nightclub)|Amnesia]]'s weekly "Foam and Diamonds" parties on [[Ibiza]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amnesia.es/webapp/Paris-Hilton-presents-Foam--Diamonds-news.en.html?mcon_id=4467 |title=Amnesia Ibiza: the best global club of Ibiza |publisher=Amnesia.es |date=August 29, 2013 |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/code/1717656/paris-hilton-to-perform-as-resident-dj-at-amnesia-ibizas-foam-party |title=Paris Hilton To Perform As Resident DJ At Amnesia Ibiza's Foam Party |publisher=Billboard |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref> The positive reaction from critics and audiences led to her contract's renewal for the subsequent four years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/paris-hilton-djs-ibiza-amnesia-2120228 |title=Paris Hilton DJs in Ibiza at Amnesia - Johnny Lee - 3am & Mirror Online |publisher=Mirror.co.uk |date=August 3, 2013 |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vibe.com/article/paris-hilton-dj-contract-amnesia-nightclub |title=Paris Hilton Inks Major DJ Contract |publisher=Vibe |date=August 29, 2013 |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref> In October, Hilton released the first single through Cash Money, "[[Good Time (Paris Hilton song)|Good Time]]", featuring rapper [[Lil Wayne]].<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/music/news/a501515/paris-hilton-shoots-new-music-video-its-amazing.html |title=Paris Hilton shoots new music video: 'It's amazing' - Music News |publisher=Digital Spy |date=July 26, 2013 |accessdate=September 13, 2013}}</ref> It debuted at number eighteen on the US ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Dance/Electronic Songs]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/code/5762990/diplo-paris-hilton-lady-gaga-debut-on-dance-charts |title=Diplo, Paris Hilton, Lady Gaga Debut On Dance Charts |publisher=Billboard |accessdate=April 3, 2014}}</ref> In November, Hilton won the Best Breakthrough DJ award at the NRJ DJ Awards.

In March 2014, Hilton unveiled her first real estate project, the Paris Beach Club, in collaboration with Century Properties Group, Inc., at the Azure Urban Resort Residences in [[Parañaque]], the Philippines.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://philnews.ph/2014/03/13/paris-hilton-leads-paris-beach-club-inauguration/|title=Paris Hilton leads Paris Beach Club inauguration - Philippine News|date=March 13, 2014|publisher=}}</ref> In July 2014, her next single, "[[Come Alive (Paris Hilton song)|Come Alive]]", was released,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Goodman|first1=Jessica|title=Paris Hilton's 'Come Alive' Music Video Is An Absurd Fairytale Rave|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/07/15/paris-hilton-come-alive-music-video_n_5589255.html|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=August 2, 2014|date=July 15, 2014}}</ref> and she made a cameo appearance in another [[Carl's Jr.]] commercial, paying homage to the one in which she starred in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popsugar.com/celebrity/Paris-Hilton-Carl-Jr-Commercial-2014-35320760|title=Paris Hilton Throws Back to 2005 in a New Carl's Jr. Commercial|first=Lauren|last=Turner|publisher=}}</ref> By the end of 2014, she established herself as one of the highest-paid DJs, earning up to US$1 million for set;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/oct/23/paris-hilton-earns-up-to-1m-single-dj-set|title=Paris Hilton earns up to $1m for a single DJ set|first=Sean|last=Michaels|date=October 23, 2014|website=the Guardian}}</ref> she also won as Best Female DJ at the NJR DJ Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/various-artists-1680-1221399#Vy1CbJYXwbOhOgJK.99|title=Paris Hilton wins 'Best Female DJ' award - NME|date=November 14, 2014|publisher=}}</ref>

In March 2015, Hilton released her 19th fragrance, a limited edition of her second fragrance, Heiress,<ref name="vice"/> and Animoca Brands, a mobile game developer from Hong Kong, announced that they had secured a license from Hilton to use her name and likeness to produce mobile games and themes.<ref name=games>{{cite news|title=Paris Hilton Getting New Video Game|author=Eddie Makuch|date=March 3, 2015|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/paris-hilton-getting-new-video-game/1100-6425667/|publisher=Gamespot}}</ref> In May, her third single under Cash Money, "[[High Off My Love]]", was released. It eventually peaked at number three on the ''Billboard'' US [[Dance Club Songs]] chart. In 2016, Hilton teamed up with [[Lidl]] for a hair care collection,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.ie/style/beauty/hair/paris-hilton-has-teamed-up-with-lidl-to-release-a-hair-care-range-35312019.html|title=Paris Hilton has teamed up with Lidl to release a hair care range|work=Independent.ie}}</ref> and released her 20th fragrance, Gold Rush;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allure.com/story/paris-hilton-perfume-gold-rush|title=Paris Hilton Continues World Beauty Domination|first=Elizabeth|last=Denton|publisher=}}</ref> she subsequently released Rosé Rush, in 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/Paris-Hilton/Ros-Rush-45571.html|title=Rosé Rush Paris Hilton perfume - a new fragrance for women 2017|website=www.fragrantica.com}}</ref> and Platinum Rush, in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fragrantica.com/perfume/Paris-Hilton/Platinum-Rush-50794.html|title=Platinum Rush Paris Hilton perfume - a new fragrance for women 2018|website=www.fragrantica.com}}</ref>

In February 2017, Hilton walked the runway at Christian Cowan’s fall show in New York City.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2017/02/11/paris-hilton-is-back-because-fashion-just-cant-help-itself/|title=Paris Hilton is back. Because fashion just can’t help itself.|work=Washington Post}}</ref> She appeared in the video for the [[Demi Lovato]] song "[[Sorry Not Sorry (Demi Lovato song)|Sorry Not Sorry]]", which premiered in July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7873039/demi-lovato-paris-hilton-jamie-foxx-wiz-khalifa-sorry-not-sorry-video-tease|title=Demi Lovato Invites Paris Hilton, Jamie Foxx & Wiz Khalifa to 'Sorry Not Sorry' House Party Teaser: Watch|publisher=}}</ref> In September 2017, she modeled at the [[Philipp Plein]] show during [[Milan Fashion Week]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/paris-hilton-talks-after-modeling-in-philipp-pleins-show-in-milan|title=Paris Hilton Talks After Modeling in Philipp Plein's Show in Milan|first=Sarah|last=Leon|publisher=}}</ref> A video for "[[I Don't Want It at All]]", the debut single of [[Kim Petras]], was released in October featuring Hilton in a cameo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2017/10/30/kim-petras-i-dont-want-it-at-all-video-paris-hilton/|title=Kim Petras parties with Paris Hilton in dreamy 'I Don't Want It At All' video|publisher=}}</ref>

In January 2018, Hilton modeled [[Kanye West]]'s [[Adidas Yeezy|Yeezy]] Season 6 collection by recreating paparazzi photos of [[Kim Kardashian]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/models/a15940678/paris-hilton-yeezy-season-6-campaign/|title=Paris Hilton Is a Kim Kardashian Clone for the Yeezy Season 6 Campaign|date=January 31, 2018|publisher=}}</ref> She released "[[I Need You (Paris Hilton song)|I Need You]]" as a [[Digital download (music)|digital download]] on February 14, 2018 ([[Valentine's Day]]).<ref name="Source18">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-need-you-single/1345742865|title=I Need You - Single|date=February 14, 2018|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180401213252/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-need-you-single/1345742865|archivedate=April 1, 2018|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Source3">{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/paris-hilton-single-i-need-you-fiance-chris-zylka-inspired/|title=Paris Hilton's New Single 'I Need You' Is Inspired by Her 'Perfect' Fiancé Chris Zylka|last=Sands|first=Nicole|date=February 14, 2018|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180401083322/http://people.com/music/paris-hilton-single-i-need-you-fiance-chris-zylka-inspired/|archivedate=April 1, 2018|deadurl=no}}</ref> It debuted at number 48 and peaked at number 32 on the [[Dance Club Songs]] [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'' chart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8356579/billboard-dance-chart-upstarts-azealia-banks-yellow-claw-paris-hilton|title=Billboard Dance Chart Upstarts: Azealia Banks, Yellow Claw & Paris Hilton|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Paris-Hilton/chart-history/dance-club-play-songs|title=Paris Hilton Chart History|publisher=}}</ref> She subsequently appeared in two social media themed-projects; the documentary ''[[The American Meme]]'' premiered at the 2018 [[Tribeca Film Festival]],<ref>Owen Gleiberman, [https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/the-american-meme-review-1202793778/ "Tribeca Film Review: ‘The American Meme’,"] ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', May 1, 2018.</ref>  and the series ''[[Hollywood Love Story]]'' aired on [[Viceland]], starting in July 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/tv/paris-hilton-hollywood-love-story-trailer/|title=Paris Hilton Explores the Complexities of Internet Fame in New Show Hollywood Love Story|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=July 22, 2018|language=en}}</ref>

Hilton and [[Boohoo.com]] collaborated on a 70-piece collection, which launched on June 20, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.glamour.com/gallery/paris-hilton-collection-for-boohoo|title=Paris Hilton Designed a Very Paris Hilton Fashion Line|first=Condé|last=Nast|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/p/whats-in-the-paris-hilton-x-boohoo-collection-your-inner-2000s-kid-is-so-ready-for-these-tracksuits-9368641|title=Paris Hilton Is Launching A Clothing Collab & The Early 2000s Are Back, Baby|first=Amy|last=Sciarretto|publisher=}}</ref> After releasing the "Unicorn Mist" rose water in late 2017, she launched a skincare line on June 29, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/paris-hilton-skincare-line-launch|title=Paris Hilton's New Skincare Line Will Have You Wondering What Year It Is|first=Zoë|last=Weiner|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jannamandell/2017/11/30/paris-hilton-launches-skincare-line-with-unicorn-mist-cue-shocked-face/|title=Paris Hilton Launches Skincare Line With Unicorn Mist; Cue Shocked Face|first=Janna|last=Mandell|publisher=}}</ref> Hilton modeled The Blonds show and opened the show for Namalia during [[New York Fashion Week]] in September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BnhBnyaH2QE/?hl=en&taken-by=parishilton|title=Paris Hilton on Instagram: "Slaying the @TheBlondsNY #DisneyVillainsXTheBlonds runway show with @DiamondBabyX. 🔥💃🏼🔥 #NYFW"|website=Instagram}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BnopyYXnp73/?hl=en&taken-by=parishilton|title=Paris Hilton on Instagram: "Opening the runway show for @_Namilia_ last night as the #RedAngelofLove 🔥💃🏼🔥 #NYFW 🗽 #ThatsHot"|website=Instagram}}</ref>

==Public image==
===General===
[[File:Paris Hilton 3 Crop.jpg|thumb|upright|alt=Young blonde woman with blue eyes|Hilton in 2006]]
A fixture in entertainment news for her late-night persona by 2001,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2011/11/02/showbiz/celebrity-news-gossip/jason-moore-on-paris-hilton/index.html |title=The man who 'made' Paris Hilton - CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date=November 2, 2011 |accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref> Hilton attracted widespread notoriety for her participation in ''[[1 Night in Paris]]'' (a sex tape leaked before the first episode of ''The Simple Life'') in late 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/fox-the-simple-life-premiere-draws-13-million-viewers-and-night-highest-adults-18-49-rating-2050.php |title=FOX's 'The Simple Life' premiere draws 13 million viewers and the night's highest Adults 18-49 rating |publisher=Reality TV World |accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref> [[Paparazzi]] mobs started to follow her, and her relationships and lifestyle in general became targets of gossip sites and [[tabloid journalism|tabloid media]] worldwide. Critics suggest that Hilton epitomizes being [[famous for being famous]],<ref name="phfame" /> exemplifying the ''[[celebutante]]'' phenomenon—a celebrity for no particularly identifiable reason other than inherited wealth and lavish lifestyle. She has been credited with influencing the revival of the term during the early-to-mid 2000s, and once remarked: "Back in the day, when I first came into this world, there was no one like it. It was almost like creating a new genre, and I think before its time. [...] Now we see it all coming back, and everyone’s calling me the OG, and it’s like, yeah. It feels really good".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/music/2017/08/05/paris-hilton-ibiza-dj-interview/|title=Paris Hilton on How to Get Paid to Party|publisher=}}</ref>

In 2004, Hilton was named one of the "10 Most Fascinating People", according to [[Barbara Walters]]' annual primetime
special ("Paris' Most Shocking Moments").<ref>https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/62641600.pdf</ref> She ranked 59th, 23rd, 34th and 35th in ''[[FHM]]''{{'}}s [[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|100 Sexiest Women]] poll in 2004, 2005, 2006 and 2012, respectively,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/paris-hilton |title=Paris Hilton &#124; Heir We Go &#124; Girls We Love |publisher=FHM.com |accessdate=April 3, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530173909/http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/paris-hilton |archivedate=May 30, 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2012/05/02/fhm-100-sexiest-women-2012-rihanna-selena-gomez-kim-kardashian-kristen-stewart/ |title=FHM Sexiest Women In The World 2012 — See Who Tops The List |publisher=Hollywood Life |date=May 2, 2012 |accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/news/fhms-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2012-the-full-list--83154 |title=FHM's 100 Sexiest Women In The World 2012: The full list! &#124; Girls |publisher=FHM.com |accessdate=September 2, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120505121053/http://www.fhm.com/girls/news/fhms-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2012-the-full-list--83154 |archivedate=May 5, 2012 }}</ref> and was 20th and 38th on ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' magazine's Hot 100 list in 2005 and 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxim.com/hot-100/2005-hot-100|title=2005 Hot 100|publisher=Maxim|date=May 1, 2005|accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxim.com/funny/the-2006-hot-100-list|title=The 2006 Hot 100 List|publisher=Maxim|accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref> In a poll conducted by the [[Associated Press]] and [[AOL]] Hilton was the second-Worst Celebrity Role Model of 2006, behind [[Britney Spears]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Spears and Hilton Named Worst Role Models| work=The Daily Dish|date=December 29, 2006|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/blogs/sfgate/detail?blogid=7&entry_id=12182|accessdate=June 10, 2007}}</ref> Lloyd Grove banned her from his ''[[New York Daily News]]'' gossip column, and in February 2007 the [[Associated Press]] attempted to not mention her for a week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/television/2007-03-01-919715477_x.htm|title=Even ignoring Paris Hilton makes news|author=Jocelyn Noveck|agency=Associated Press|date=March 1, 2007|accessdate=May 5, 2007|work=USA Today}}</ref> In May Hilton denied calling herself the "iconic blonde of the decade", like [[Diana, Princess of Wales|Princess Diana]] and [[Marilyn Monroe]], in ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://women.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/women/celebrity/article684740.ece|title=We'll Always Have Paris|newspaper=[[The Times]]|accessdate=April 3, 2014|location=London}} {{subscription required}}</ref> She appeared in the 2007 ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as the world's Most Overrated Celebrity.<ref>Maher, Kevin. "The Paris-bashing should stop here." ''[[The Times]] (London).'' March 20, 2008, p. 16. Retrieved May 13, 2008. "Guinness World Records has her as the World's Most Overrated Celebrity."</ref><ref>Gumbel, Andrew. "Paris Hilton is granted a shorter sentence&nbsp;— if she behaves herself." ''[[The Independent]]'' (London, UK). May 18, 2007, p. 1; retrieved May 13, 2008. "She is set to appear in this year's Guinness World Records as the world's 'most overrated celebrity'."</ref>

In 2009, a quiet relationship between Hilton and the tabloids led entertainment writers to suggest that her popularity had waned; she was the subject of a   [[CNN]] story, asking, "Why has Paris Hilton disappeared?". This suspicion was reinforced in June 2011 when her reality show, ''The World According to Paris'', had low ratings and Hilton walked out during an interview with ''[[Good Morning America]]'' when asked if she worried about her moment having passed.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2011/07/20/paris-hilton-storms-out-good-morning-america-interview-over-questions-about-her/ |title=Paris Hilton Storms Out of 'Good Morning America' Interview Over Questions About Her Fame |publisher=Fox News |accessdate=August 10, 2012 |date=July 20, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Schwartz |first=Alison |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20511528,00.html |title=Paris Hilton Walks Out of Interview with ABC News – Scandals & Feuds, Good Morning America, Paris Hilton |work=People |date=July 20, 2011 |accessdate=August 10, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120204113/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20511528,00.html |archivedate=November 20, 2012  }}</ref> However, following her involvement with the filming of ''The Bling Ring'' and her deal with [[Cash Money Records]] in 2013, she became a trending topic worldwide on Twitter<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ok.co.uk/celebrity-news/view/63350/Paris-Hilton-music-deal-news-sends-Twitter-into-meltdown|title=Paris Hilton music deal news sends Twitter into meltdown|publisher=Ok.co.uk|date=May 23, 2013|accessdate=September 2, 2013}}</ref> and media outlets noted 2013 as Hilton's "pop culture renaissance" year.

In 2011, Hilton was named one of the 100 Hottest Women of All Time by ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]'',<ref name="phlist">{{cite web|title=The 100 Hottest Women of All-Time|url=http://www.menshealth.com/sex-women/hottest-women-all-time|work=[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]|accessdate=January 3, 2012|year=2011}}</ref> but according to an [[Ipsos]] poll she was the most unpopular celebrity with Americans (with 60 percent of respondents viewing her unfavorably).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ipsos-na.com/news-polls/pressrelease.aspx?id=5306 |title=Betty White Is America's Favorite and Most Trusted Personality, and the Most Prone to Driving Brand Purchase |work=ipsos.com |date=August 18, 2011 |accessdate=August 21, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110918023115/http://www.ipsos-na.com/news-polls/pressrelease.aspx?id=5306 |archivedate=September 18, 2011 |df= }}</ref> In 2012, she ranked fifth on ''[[Forbes]]''{{'}} Most Over-Exposed list.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://marquee.blogs.cnn.com/2012/03/29/america-say-hello-to-your-overexposed-celebs/|title=America, say hello to your overexposed celebs|publisher=CNN|accessdate=May 19, 2012|date=March 29, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/mfl45jhei/paris-hilton|title=Paris Hilton - In Photos: The Most Overexposed Celebrities|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=September 2, 2013 |first=Dorothy |last=Pomerantz}}</ref>

==="That's hot" catchphrase===
The catchphrase "That's hot" is Hilton's signature line.<ref name="hot n not">{{cite book |first=Katarina |last=Rasulić |year=2015 |chapter=What's Hot and What's Not in English and Serbian |chapterurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=_PyADQAAQBAJ&lpg=PA290&dq=%22Paris%20Hilton%22%20%22that's%20hot%22%20signature&pg=PA290#v=onepage&q=%22Paris%20Hilton%22%20%22that's%20hot%22%20signature&f=false |title=The Linguistics of Temperature |editor=Maria Koptjevskaja-Tamm |publisher=[[John Benjamins Publishing Company]] |location=[[Amsterdam]], Netherlands |page=290 |issn=0167-7373 |isbn=978-90-272-0688-6 |lccn=2014035097 |accessdate=January 16, 2017 |via=Google Books }}</ref> The catchphrase is also registered as a trademark for products, like clothing apparel, electronic devices, and alcoholic beverages.<ref name="hot n not"/>

On September 6, 2007, Hilton filed an [[injunction]] lawsuit against [[Hallmark Cards]] Inc., titled ''Hilton v. Hallmark Cards'', in [[U.S. District Court]] over the unlawful use of her picture and catchphrase "That's hot" on a greeting card. The card is titled "Paris's First Day as a Waitress" with a photograph of Hilton's face on a cartoon of a waitress serving a plate of food, with a dialogue bubble saying "Don't touch that, it's hot" (which had a [[registered trademark]] on February 13, 2007). Hilton's attorney Brent Blakely said that the [[Copyright infringement|infringement]] damages would be based on profits from the greeting cards. Julie O'Dell said that Hallmark used the card as [[parody]], protected under [[fair use]] law.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thesmokinggun.com/documents/celebrity/paris-hilton-sues-over-hallmark-card | title=Paris Hilton Sues Over Hallmark Card | work=The Smoking Gun | date=September 7, 2007 | accessdate=December 12, 2008}}</ref> The [[United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit|Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit]] reviewed the case and "denied Hallmark's motion to dismiss". Hilton and Hallmark Cards Inc. later [[Settlement (litigation)|settled out of court]].<ref>{{cite book |first=T. |last=Carter |author2=Juliet Lushbough Dee |author3=Harvey L. Zuckman |year=2014 |orig-year=1983 |title=Mass Communication Law in a Nutshell |edition=7th |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sVDaCgAAQBAJ&lpg=PT126&dq=%22Paris%20Hilton%22%20%22that's%20hot%22%20hallmark%20cards&pg=PT127#v=onepage&q=%22Paris%20Hilton%22%20%22that's%20hot%22%20hallmark%20cards&f=false |publisher=West Publishing Co. |location=[[St. Paul, Minnesota]] |isbn=978-0-314-28063-3 |accessdate=February 9, 2017 }}</ref>

===In popular culture===
Hilton has had two popular television characters loosely based on her real-life persona: [[London Tipton]] from ''[[The Suite Life of Zack & Cody]]'' (Tipton's father in the series is a hotel mogul) and Caroline Channing in ''[[2 Broke Girls]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pluggedin.com/tv/0-9/2brokegirls.aspx|title=2 Broke Girls TV Review - Plugged In|website=www.pluggedin.com}}</ref>

The ''[[World of Warcraft]]'' [[massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] has featured a character named Haris Pilton, labeled a "socialite", since the release of ''[[World of Warcraft: The Burning Crusade|The Burning Crusade]]'' expansion on January 15, 2007. The character remains in the game as of April 2015.<ref>[http://www.wowhead.com/npc=18756/haris-pilton Haris Pilton], accessed April 29, 2015</ref>

Hilton has been parodied in the ''[[South Park]]'' episode "[[Stupid Spoiled Whore Video Playset]]" (2004),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/tvandradioblog/2009/dec/29/best-tv-episodes-noughties|title=What are the best TV episodes of the noughties?|first=Richard|last=Vine|date=December 29, 2009|website=the Guardian}}</ref> and in the Hollywood films ''[[White Chicks]]'' (2004),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.daily-journal.com/entertainment/wayans-brothers-imitate-hilton-sisters-in-white-chicks/article_2978e09e-7c7c-522a-a6da-736544259bd4.html|title=Wayans brothers imitate Hilton sisters in 'White Chicks'|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[Date Movie]]'' (2006),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2006/02/18/date-movie|title=Date Movie - IGN|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[Epic Movie]]'' (2007),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0799949/fullcredits|title=Epic Movie (2007)|publisher=|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref> and ''[[Meet the Spartans]]'' (2008).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/film/2008/mar/23/comedy.features|title=Review: Meet the Spartans|first=Philip|last=French|date=March 23, 2008|website=the Guardian}}</ref> In 2007, she was the subject of the [[Youtube]] spoof video "Paris in Jail", inspired by her single "Stars Are Blind", which had been played more than 7 million times by the first month of its publishing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-2007-07-04-0707020280-story.html|title=For Paris, the best defense is parody|first=Steve Johnson, Tribune Internet|last=critic|publisher=}}</ref> Amber Hay, the actress who portrayed Hilton in the aforementioned video, also portrayed her in the made-for-television film ''Paparazzi Princess: The Paris Hilton Story'' (2008).<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1109600/</ref>

==Personal life==
Hilton lives in [[Mulholland Estates]],<ref name="varietyparishiltonsnewpad" /> a gated community in [[Los Angeles]], California.<ref>paris-hilton-buys-5-9m-beverly-hills-house/</ref> She also has a penthouse in [[Lower Manhattan]], NYC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/dirt/real-estalker/paris-hilton-picks-up-downtown-manhattan-penthouse-1201355797/|title=Paris Hilton Picks Up Downtown Manhattan Penthouse|first=Mark|last=David|date=November 13, 2014|publisher=}}</ref>

Hilton is known for her love of small dogs, and has had a female [[Chihuahua (dog)|Chihuahua]] named Tinkerbell among many other pets. Hilton was frequently seen carrying Tinkerbell (dubbed an "accessory dog") at social events and functions, and in all five seasons of television reality show ''The Simple Life''.<ref>{{Cite news| title=A happy ending for Tinkerbell |work=USA Today  |date=August 18, 2004|accessdate=September 21, 2006|url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2004-08-18-hilton-dog_x.htm|first1=Karen|last1=Thomas}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/blogs/sfgate/detail?blogid=7&entry_id=18916|title=Hilton Buys a Dog From Spears' Pet Shop|work=San Francisco Chronicle|publisher=World Entertainment News Network|accessdate=July 26, 2007|first=Karen|last=Reardanz|date=July 26, 2007}}</ref> In September 2014, she bought a [[Pomeranian dog]], worth US$13,000,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/578888/paris-hilton-buys-tiny-13-000-puppy-a-white-pomeranian-see-the-photos|title=Paris Hilton Buys $13,000 Pomeranian Puppy—See the Photos!|date=September 12, 2014|publisher=}}</ref> and in January 2015, she spent US$25,000 in two other, for herself and for her mother as a 35th anniversary gift.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2015/01/07/paris-hilton-new-dogs-pomeranians-mom-dog/|title=Paris Hilton -- Drops $25K for One Pound of Dog|publisher=}}</ref> In April 2015, it was reported that Tinkerbell had died at the age of 14.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/rest-peace-tinkerbell-paris-hiltons-starlet-dog/story?id=30491650|title=Rest in Peace Tinkerbell, Paris Hilton's Starlet Dog|last=Good|first=Dan|date=April 22, 2015|access-date=April 22, 2015|via=|work=[[ABC News]]|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]}}</ref> For her pets, a 300-square-foot home with air conditioning, heating and designer furniture was built at an estimated cost of US$325,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elledecor.com/celebrity-style/celebrity-homes/a12119195/paris-hilton-dog-house/|title=Paris Hilton’s #DoggyMansion Is Probably Nicer Than Your House|date=August 29, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/pets/paris-hilton-dog-house/|title=Paris Hilton's Dogs Have a Nicer House Than You (See Photos)|publisher=}}</ref>

[[File:Paris Hilton at Sundance Film Festival 2008.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Hilton at the 2008 [[Sundance Film Festival]]]]
On January 22, 2007, her private life became public on ParisExposed.com, a website with images of personal documents, video and other material allegedly obtained when the contents of a storage locker rented by Hilton were auctioned in lieu of a US$208 payment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/article/0,,4-2007040270,00.html|location=London, UK|work=The Sun|first=Emily|last=Smith|title=Paris Hiltons new sex tape|date=May 10, 2007|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071002100351/http://www.thesun.co.uk/article/0,,4-2007040270,00.html|archivedate=October 2, 2007}}</ref> The website, which charged for online access to the material, had 1.2&nbsp;million visitors in just over 40 hours.<ref>Thomas, Karen. (January 30, 2007) [https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2007-01-25-hilton-website_x.htm?POE=LIFISVA Paris Hilton website exposed]. Usatoday.com; retrieved December 27, 2010.</ref> Among its contents were medications, diaries, photographs, contracts, love letters and a video shot by [[Joe Francis]] of [[Girls Gone Wild (franchise)|Girls Gone Wild]].<ref>[http://www.vnunet.com/vnunet/news/2173542/paris-hilton-effects-online Paris Hilton videos exposed online]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080930091730/http://www.vnunet.com/vnunet/news/2173542/paris-hilton-effects-online |date=September 30, 2008 }}, Vnunet.com; retrieved December 27, 2010.</ref> Hilton obtained a temporary injunction against ParisExposed.com which shut down the website.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Site barred from releasing Hilton data|date=February 3, 2007|url=https://www.usatoday.com/tech/news/2007-02-05-paris-website_x.htm|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=February 9, 2007|work=USA Today}}</ref>

Between 2008 and 2009, Hilton's home was burgled several times by the [[Bling Ring]], a group of fashion-motivated thieves. It was not until nearly US$2 million were stolen in jewelry, clothing, cash, and other items from Hilton that she reported having been burgled.<ref>{{cite news|author=Linda Massarella |author2=Todd Venezia |url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/national/thief_is_sole_mate_to_hilton_OBbA0rRllKe8aPfnS6qWsO |title='Thief' is sole mate to Hilton |work=[[New York Post]] |date=October 25, 2009 |accessdate=January 6, 2012}}</ref> Later, Hilton agreed to having the movie ''The Bling Ring'' shot in her house where the burglaries took place.

On September 20, 2012, an audio recording of Hilton making derogatory comments about gay people was posted on the Internet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/09/paris-hilton-gays-disgusting-most-probably-have-aids|title=Paris Hilton: Gays 'Disgusting', Most 'Probably Have AIDS'|publisher=Abcnews.go.com|date=September 20, 2012|accessdate=December 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/09/21/showbiz/paris-hilton-gays/index.html|title=Paris Hilton apologizes for calling gay men 'disgusting'|publisher=Edition.cnn.com|accessdate=June 16, 2013|date=September 21, 2012}}</ref> That day, following a backlash, she issued an apology through [[GLAAD]] in which she said she was a "huge supporter of the gay community" and called gay people "the strongest and most inspiring people I know".<ref>{{cite web|last=Abbey|first=Jennifer|url=http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/09/paris-hilton-apologizes-gay-people-are-the-strongest|title=Paris Hilton Apologizes: 'Gay People Are the Strongest'|publisher=Abcnews.go.com|date=September 21, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2012/sep/21/entertainment/la-et-mg-paris-hilton-apologizes-gay-comments-20120921|title=Paris Hilton apologizes for anti-gay sex and AIDS comments|publisher=Articles.latimes.com|date=September 21, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013|first=Christie|last=D'Zurilla}}</ref> As a result of her remarks, [[Logo TV]] canceled plans to air a documentary about her (''Paris Hilton Inc'').<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/348754/paris-hilton-documentary-shelved-by-gay-channel-following-celebutante-s-homophobic-tiradez|title=Paris Hilton Documentary Shelved By Gay Channel Following Celebutantes Homophobic Tirade|publisher=E! Online|date=September 25, 2012|accessdate=December 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Dish|first=Daily |url=http://blog.sfgate.com/dailydish/2012/09/26/logo-axes-paris-hilton-show-after-aids-comments-backlash|title=Logo axes Paris Hilton show after AIDS comments backlash|publisher=Blog.sfgate.com|date=September 26, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/logo-drops-paris-hilton-schedule-373980|title=Logo Drops Paris Hilton From Schedule in Wake of Offensive Comments|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=September 25, 2012|accessdate=June 16, 2013|first=Seth|last=Abramovitch}}</ref>

Hilton has a pink [[Bentley Continental]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/06/paris-hilton-barbie-pink-bentley_n_4737432.html|title=Paris Hilton Channels Barbie In Her Pink Bentley|date=February 6, 2014|publisher=|via=Huff Post}}</ref> another Bentley convertible,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autoloandaily.com/paris-hilton-baby-blue-bentley/|title=Paris Hilton’s Baby Blue Bentley - Auto Loan Daily|website=www.autoloandaily.com}}</ref> a [[Rolls-Royce Ghost]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autoevolution.com/news/paris-hilton-in-a-brand-new-rolls-royce-ghost-27947.html|title=Paris Hilton in a Brand New Rolls Royce Ghost|first=Bogdan|last=Popa|date=December 9, 2010|publisher=}}</ref> a [[Ferrari]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/276963/paris-hilton-snags-a-red-ferrari-on-black-friday|title=Paris Hilton Snags a Red Ferrari on Black Friday|date=November 26, 2011|publisher=}}</ref> a [[Lexus]] coupe,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorauthority.com/news/1055487_paris-hilton-gets-lexus-lfa-for-30th-birthday|title=Paris Hilton Gets Lexus LFA For 30th Birthday|publisher=}}</ref> and a Yukon Hybrid.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2008/03/06/hilton-hybrid-hypocrite/|title=Hilton: Hybrid Hypocrite?|publisher=}}</ref>

===Relationships===
Throughout her life, Hilton's personal life, and especially her extensive list of relationships and romantic associations with other high-profile figures, has drawn a large amount of media attention and public disapproval.<ref>https://galoremag.com/paris-hiltons-dating-history/</ref> In 2000, for instance, the then-19-year-old rose tabloids' attention when she and [[Leonardo DiCaprio]] were seen together on the NYC late-night circuit. That led to Hilton adamantly deny to ''Vanity Fair'', in one of her first magazine profiles, that they were involved.<ref>https://www.eonline.com/news/903420/paris-hilton-s-epic-romantic-history-all-the-hookups-breakups-drama-you-forgot-about</ref> She dated actor [[Edward Furlong]] in 2000, and poker player [[Rick Salomon]], with whom she filmed her sex tape, circa early 2000s.<ref name="usmag">https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/pictures/paris-hiltons-complete-dating-history/josh-henderson-4/</ref> She was engaged to fashion model Jason Shaw from 2002 to 2003.<ref>{{cite news|last=Parvizi|first=Lauren|url=http://blog.sfgate.com/dailydish/2010/04/30/paris-hilton-confirms-she-and-ex-jason-shaw-are-very-close|title=Paris Hilton confirms she and ex Jason Shaw are 'very close'|publisher=Blog.sfgate.com|date=April 30, 2010|accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> They have reportedly remained friends since their split. She had a seven-month relationship with singer [[Nick Carter (musician)|Nick Carter]] in 2004;<ref>{{cite news|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/people/2004-07-26-parisnick-breakup_x.htm |title=Paris Hilton and Nick Carter break up |publisher=USAToday.com |date=July 26, 2004 |accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> Carter opened up about their relationship in his 2013 autobiography. "Paris was the worst person in the world for me to hook up with," he wrote. "[She] fed my worst impulses as far as partying."<ref name="usmag" />  

Hilton started dating Greek shipping heir [[Paris Latsis]] in December 2004,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realitytvworld.com/news/simple-life-star-paris-hilton-breaks-off-engagement-paris-latsis-1004857.php |title='Simple Life' star Paris Hilton breaks off engagement to Paris Latsis |publisher=Reality TV World |accessdate=January 30, 2013}}</ref> and both became engaged seven months later.<ref name="usmag" /> In November 2005, however, they called the impending nuptials off.<ref name="usmag" /> She next had a relationship with another Greek heir, Stavros Nicharos, who she dated on and off until March 2007.<ref name="usmag" /> Hilton dated [[Good Charlotte]] guitarist [[Benji Madden]] for nine months, until November 2008.<ref>Lansing, Kimberly. (November 19, 2008) [http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20241470,00.html Paris Hilton and Benji Madden Split Up – Breakups, Benji Madden, Paris Hilton]. People.com. Retrieved on December 27, 2010.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Paris Hilton and Benji Madden split |publisher=[[ninemsn]] |date=November 20, 2008 |accessdate=November 20, 2008 |url=http://optuszoo.news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=668775&rss=yes&_cobr=optus |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090112062224/http://optuszoo.news.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=668775&rss=yes&_cobr=optus |archivedate=January 12, 2009 |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/story/0,26278,23682775-10388,00.html Paris Hilton to wed Benji Madden]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080513064235/http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/story/0%2C26278%2C23682775-10388%2C00.html |date=May 13, 2008 }}, news.com.au; retrieved May 12, 2008.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2008/03/15/Hilton_feels_secure_with_Madden/UPI-28821205594293/ |title=Hilton feels 'secure' with Madden|date=March 15, 2008|publisher=upi.com|accessdate=March 23, 2008}}</ref> An on and off relationship with ''[[The Hills (TV series)|The Hills]]'' star [[Doug Reinhardt]] followed,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20265729,00.html|title=Paris Calls Doug Reinhardt 'My Sexy Boy'|work=PEOPLE.com|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> but they broke up definitely in April 2010, when she became concerned that he was using her to further his career.<ref>https://metro.co.uk/2010/04/12/paris-hilton-and-doug-reinhardt-split-234664/</ref> She would next date Las Vegas nightclub owner Cy Waits until June 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azcentral.com/ent/celeb/articles/2010/12/23/20101223paris-hilton-cy-waits-inspires-me-best-can.html|title=Paris Hilton: Cy Waits 'inspires me to be the best I can be'|publisher=|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> After her split with Waits, Hilton was rumoured to have a relationship with Dutch DJ [[Afrojack]],<ref>http://articles.nydailynews.com/2012-05-31/news/31931321_1_socialite-tweeted-relationship-paris-hilton</ref> but he distanced himself amid her growing DJ career.<ref name="usmag" /> She had a relationship with Spanish model River Viiperi between 2012 and 2014,<ref>https://www.eonline.com/photos/23378/paris-hilton-s-romantic-history/816981</ref> and dated businessman Thomas Gross between 2015 and April 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/759283/paris-hilton-and-boyfriend-thomas-gross-break-up-after-a-year-of-dating|title=Paris Hilton and Boyfriend Thomas Gross Break Up|date=April 23, 2016|publisher=}}</ref>

Actor [[Chris Zylka]] proposed to her with a ring worth US$2 million in January 2018, during a vacation in [[Aspen]], after one year of dating.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://people.com/style/paris-hilton-chris-zylka-engaged/|title=Paris Hilton and Chris Zylka Are Engaged: 'I Have Never Felt So Happy'|first1=Julie|last1=Jordan|first2=Maria|last2=Pasquini|date=January 2, 2018 |accessdate=April 1, 2018|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]| archivedate=January 2, 2018 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20180102164416/http://people.com/style/paris-hilton-chris-zylka-engaged/ |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bdc913pn0MZ/|first=Paris|last=Hilton|date= January 2, 2018| accessdate=April 1, 2018|publisher=Paris Hilton verified [[Instagram]] account| title=I said Yas!|quote=So happy & excited to be engaged to the love of my life.}}</ref> They called off their engagement in November 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/a25226341/paris-hilton-chris-zylka-breakup/|title=Paris Hilton and Chris Zylka Have Ended Their Engagement|date=November 19, 2018|work=ELLE|access-date=November 20, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>

===Sex tape===
In 2003, a [[celebrity sex tape|sex tape]] featuring Hilton and then-boyfriend Rick Salomon was leaked onto the Internet. Shortly afterward, Salomon filed a lawsuit against the company that distributed the tape, and against the Hilton family, whom he accused of tarnishing his reputation by suggesting that he had exploited Hilton.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,544778,00.html|title=Shame Game |last=Hiatt|first=Brian |date=November 18, 2003|publisher=ew.com|accessdate=December 7, 2008}}</ref> Hilton later sued the company that released the tape, Kahatani Ltd., for $30 million for violation of privacy and emotional distress.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2004/TECH/internet/02/09/paris.lawsuit.reut/|title=Paris Hilton sues over Internet sex tape|date=February 9, 2004|publisher=cnn.com|accessdate=December 7, 2008}}</ref>

In April 2004, Salomon began distributing the tape himself through the adult film company [[Red Light District Video]] under the title ''[[1 Night in Paris]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,630669,00.html|title=X-Rated Paris Tape Goes to Home Video|last=Silverman|first=Stephen M. |date=April 30, 2004|publisher=people.com|accessdate=December 7, 2008}}</ref> In July 2004, Salomon dropped his lawsuit against the Hilton family after Paris Hilton's privacy lawsuit was thrown out of court. Salomon and Red Light District Video agreed to pay Hilton US$400,000 plus a percentage of the tape's sale profit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,663340,00.html|title='Simple' Math |last=Susman|first=Gary|date=July 13, 2007|publisher=ew.com|accessdate=December 7, 2008}}</ref>

===Stalking incidents===
In August 2010, a man identified as Nathan Lee Parada, was arrested after security men spotted him wielding two knives outside Hilton's house.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/gossip/2010/08/paris-hilton-break-in-attempt-man-charged.html|title=Nathan Lee Parada charged in Paris Hilton break-in|date=August 27, 2010|publisher=}}</ref> He was later found guilty of one felony count of attempted first-degree residential burglary, and was sentenced to two years in state prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/250004/paris-hilton-burglar-sentenced-to-two-years-in-state-prison|title=Paris Hilton Burglar Sentenced to Two Years in State Prison|date=June 30, 2011|publisher=}}</ref>

In October 2010, a man named James Rainford allegedly bicycled past guards at the entrance to her gated community, went to her house and began pounding on her door. He was arrested, and earned three years' probation, along with a restraining order from Hilton. In April 2011, Rainford was arrested a second time for attacking her then-boyfriend Cy Waits outside Van Nuys Superior Court, where Hilton was headed to testify against Nathan Lee Parada, and in July, he was arrested again outside her [[Malibu, California|Malibu]] beach house.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/paris-hiltons-accused-stalker-to-stand-trial/|title=Paris Hilton's accused stalker to stand trial|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/gossip/2011/07/paris-hilton-stalker-intruder-james-rainford-cy-waits.html|title=Paris Hilton stalker James Rainford arrested again, outside her Malibu home|date=July 5, 2011|publisher=}}</ref> He was subsequently charged with two felony stalking counts and three misdemeanor counts of disobeying a court order,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/man-is-charged-with-stalking-paris-hilton/|title=Man is charged with stalking Paris Hilton|publisher=}}</ref> but a judge found him to be "mentally incompetent to stand trial" and was sent to a state mental hospital.

In October 2014, a German man identified as Lukas Redanz, who was completely covered with tattoos of Hilton and appeared to be "extremely drunk", repeatedly went to her gated community to see her. Guards called the police and the man was arrested for possession of cocaine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2014/02/10/paris-hilton-stalker-tattoo-german/|title=Paris Hilton -- My Stalker Came Back -- He'sTatted Up With Me|publisher=}}</ref>

===Legal issues===
In September 2006, Hilton was arrested and charged with [[driving under the influence|driving under the influence of alcohol]], with a [[blood alcohol content]] of 0.08%. Hilton's driver's license was suspended in November 2006,<ref name="findlaw article"/> and in January 2007 she pleaded [[Nolo contendere|no contest]] to a [[reckless driving]] charge.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Paris Hilton's Misdemeanor DUI Charges |date=September 21, 2006|publisher=FindLaw|url =http://news.findlaw.com/cnn/docs/ent/cahilton92606cmp.html| accessdate = May 4, 2007}}</ref> Her sentence was 36 months' [[probation]] and fines totaling about US$1,500.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/16757099|title=Paris Hilton pleads no contest to DUI charge|publisher=MSNBC}}</ref> In January 2007, she was stopped for driving with a suspended license, and signed an agreement that she was not permitted to drive.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Paris Hilton checks into Los Angeles County jail|url=http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/TV/06/04/paris.hilton.ap/index.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070606085112/http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/TV/06/04/paris.hilton.ap/index.html|archivedate=June 6, 2007|date=June 4, 2007|agency=Associated Press|deadurl=yes}}</ref> The next month, she was caught driving 70&nbsp;mph in a 35-mph zone without headlights at night with a suspended license. Prosecutors in the office of the [[Los Angeles City Attorney]] charged that these infractions and her failure to enroll in a court-ordered alcohol-education program violated her probation.<ref name="findlaw article">{{Cite news|title=Prosecutors' Motion To Revoke Paris Hilton's Probation|date=April 30, 2007|publisher=FindLaw|url=http://news.findlaw.com/hdocs/docs/ent/cahilton43007mot.html|accessdate=May 4, 2007}}</ref> On May 4, Hilton was sentenced by Judge [[Michael T. Sauer]] to 45 days in jail for the probation violation. She planned to appeal the sentence, supporting an online petition (created on May 5 by Joshua Morales) asking California governor [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] for a pardon.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/americas/6637855.stm|title=Hilton backs online pardon appeal|date=May 9, 2007 |publisher=BBC News|accessdate=January 3, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20038172,00.html|title= Paris Hilton Asks For Schwarzenegger Pardon |publisher=People Magazine |date=May 8, 2007 |accessdate=May 20, 2007}}</ref> A counter-petition to maintain the sentence was posted.{{citation needed|date=August 2014}} Hilton changed lawyers and dropped her plans to appeal.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Hilton Drops Probation-Violation Appeal|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/television/2007-05-16-2294854685_x.htm|date=May 17, 2007|author=Jeremiah Marquez|agency=Associated Press|work=USA Today}}</ref>

[[File:Paris Hilton mug shot (2007).jpg|thumb|upright=.682|left|Hilton in her 2007 [[mug shot]]]]
She was required to begin her jail term on June 5,<ref name="Paris Hilton sentenced to 45 days in jail">Associated Press. [http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/TV/05/04/paris.hilton.ap/index.html Paris Hilton sentenced to 45 days in jail] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070509032551/http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/TV/05/04/paris.hilton.ap/index.html |date=May 9, 2007 }}. ''CNN''. May 5, 2007.</ref> and entered the Century Regional Detention Facility (a women's prison in [[Lynwood, California]]) after attending the [[2007 MTV Movie Awards]] on June 3. On June 7, Los Angeles County Sheriff [[Lee Baca]] signed an order resentencing Hilton to 40 days of [[House arrest|home confinement]] with an [[electronic tagging|electronic monitoring device]] due to an unspecified medical condition.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,278885,00.html|title=Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department Press Conference|work=Fox News|accessdate=September 13, 2014|date=June 7, 2007}}</ref> Baca said, "My message to those who don't like celebrities is that punishing celebrities more than the average American is not justice."<ref name="CanWest">{{Cite news|last=Deutsch |first=Linda |title=Police take Paris Hilton to court hearing Friday in Los Angeles |publisher=[[CanWest Global Communications]] |date=June 8, 2007 |url=http://www.canada.com/topics/entertainment/story.html?id=5dbfef68-cf6b-422e-902e-bb6e48db514d&k=45150&p=2 |accessdate=June 2, 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070711054325/http://www.canada.com/topics/entertainment/story.html?id=5dbfef68-cf6b-422e-902e-bb6e48db514d&k=45150&p=2 |archivedate=July 11, 2007 |df= }}</ref> He added, "The special treatment, in a sense, appears to be because of her celebrity status&nbsp;... She got more time in jail."<ref>{{Cite news|title=Early release just latest controversy for Baca|first=Michael|last=Blood|date=June 8, 2007|agency=Associated Press|url=http://www.dailynews.com/ci_6098443|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930184829/http://www.dailynews.com/ci_6098443|archivedate=September 30, 2007}}</ref> Judge Michael Sauer summoned her to reappear in court the following morning (June 8), since her original sentence specified imprisonment: "No work furlough. No work release. No electronic monitoring."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/Story?id=3254300&page=2|title=Hilton Headed Back to Jail for Full Sentence&nbsp;– ABC News|work=ABC News|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> At the hearing, Sauer declined a briefing in chambers by Hilton's attorney on her medical condition and sent her back to jail to serve the original 45-day sentence. When she heard the decision, Hilton shouted "It's not right!" Screaming, she asked to hug her mother.<ref name="cnnbacktojail">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/TV/06/08/paris.hilton.ap/index.html |title=Paris Hilton going back to jail |publisher= |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070613021424/http://www.cnn.com/2007/SHOWBIZ/TV/06/08/paris.hilton.ap/index.html |archivedate=June 13, 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tv.msn.com/tv/article.aspx?news=264863&GT1=7703&mpc=2 |title=Hilton Starts, Ends Week Behind Bars |publisher= |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070914124220/http://tv.msn.com/tv/article.aspx?news=264863&GT1=7703&mpc=2 |archivedate=September 14, 2007 }}</ref> Hilton was moved to the medical wing of the Twin Towers Correctional Facility in Los Angeles, and returned to the Century Regional Detention Facility in Lynwood on June 13.<ref>[http://news.hamsterpower.org/feeds/reuterstop/7 News Hamster]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090110224037/http://news.hamsterpower.org/feeds/reuterstop/7 |date=January 10, 2009 }}. News.hamsterpower.org (June 9, 2007). Retrieved on December 27, 2010.</ref> Paris Hilton was released from jail on Tuesday, June 26, 2007.

The socialite was influenced by minister Marty Angelo in jail, referring to a "new beginning" in an interview with talk-show host [[Larry King]] on June 28, 2007 (two days after her release)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0706/27/lkl.01.html |title=Interview With Paris Hilton |date=June 28, 2007 |publisher=CNN}}</ref> and quoting from Angelo's autobiography (''Once Life Matters: A New Beginning''). On June 9, Angelo unsuccessfully petitioned Sauer<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.martyangelo.com/judge_sauer.htm |title=Prison Minister Offers to Serve Paris Hilton's Remaining Jail Sentence |first=Marty |last=Angelo |date=June 9, 2007 |work=martyangelo.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070712133213/http://www.martyangelo.com/judge_sauer.htm |archivedate=July 12, 2007 |df= }}</ref> to let him serve the remainder of Hilton's sentence if the judge would release her to an alternative treatment program.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.emediawire.com/releases/2007/6/emw532265.htm |title=Prison Minister Offers to Serve Paris Hilton's Remaining Jail Sentence |date=June 11, 2007 |work=emediawire.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071104163410/http://www.emediawire.com/releases/2007/6/emw532265.htm |archivedate=November 4, 2007 |df= }}</ref> Hilton told King during the interview that she had taken [[Adderall]] for [[ADHD]] since childhood.<ref>{{cite book|author=J. Douglas Bremner|title=Before You Take That Pill: Why the Drug Industry May Be Bad for Your Health|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XSCqADQL8wEC&pg=PA383 |accessdate=December 18, 2011|date=February 28, 2008|publisher=Penguin |isbn=978-1-58333-295-5|pages=383–}}</ref>

On July 2, 2010, Hilton was accused of smoking marijuana at the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]] game between [[Brazil]] and the [[Netherlands]]. Although she was escorted from the [[Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium]] by local police, the case was later dismissed. Her publicist, Dawn Miller, said: "I can confirm that the incident was a complete misunderstanding and it was actually another person in the group who did it".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2010-07-02-paris-hilton-south-africa-marijuana_N.htm|title=Paris Hilton marijuana charges dropped in South Africa|publisher=|accessdate=September 13, 2014|work=USA Today|date=July 2, 2010}}</ref><ref>[http://www.timeslive.co.za/sport/soccer/article531357.ece/Paris-Hilton-arrested-at-World-Cup-stadium&nbsp;— report Paris Hilton arrested at World Cup stadium: report], timeslive.co.za, July 2, 2010.</ref> Two weeks later, Hilton was detained and released after she was caught with [[cannabis (drug)|cannabis]] at [[Corsica]]'s [[Figari Sud-Corse Airport]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.english.rfi.fr/france/20100717-hilton-held-carrying-cannabis|title=Hilton held for carrying cannabis|work=RFI|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref>

In August 2010, Hilton was arrested on suspicion of [[drug possession|cocaine possession]] in Las Vegas and her boyfriend, Cy Waits, was charged with driving under the influence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/Showbiz-News/Paris-Hilton-Is-Arrested-On-Cocaine-Charge-In-Las-Vegas-US-Police-Say/Article/201008415708305?lpos=Showbiz_News_Top_Stories_Header_1&lid=ARTICLE_15708305_Paris_Hilton_Is_Arrested_On_Cocaine_Charge_In_Las_Vegas%2C_US_Police_Say |title=Paris Hilton Arrested On Cocaine Charge |work=Sky News |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100901082354/http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/Showbiz-News/Paris-Hilton-Is-Arrested-On-Cocaine-Charge-In-Las-Vegas-US-Police-Say/Article/201008415708305?lpos=Showbiz_News_Top_Stories_Header_1&lid=ARTICLE_15708305_Paris_Hilton_Is_Arrested_On_Cocaine_Charge_In_Las_Vegas%2C_US_Police_Say |archivedate=September 1, 2010 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory?id=11502929|title='Vapor Trail' Leads to Paris Hilton's Vegas Arrest&nbsp;– ABC News|author=ABC News|work=ABC News|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> Hilton's defense initially claimed that the handbag (containing 0.8g of cocaine) was not hers: "This purse in question was a high street brand&nbsp;– and by no means up to her high fashion standards."{{cn|date=November 2018}} She later claimed personal items (including cash and credit cards) from the bag, acknowledging that it was hers. To avoid a felony conviction, Hilton pleaded guilty to two misdemeanors on September 17, 2010. Under the terms of the [[plea bargain]] she was sentenced to one year of probation, 200 hours of community service, a US$2,000 fine and the completion of a drug-abuse treatment program.<ref name="AP 2010-09-17">{{cite news|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5h_ZLksW1mXYYlB0JXdgD3Px_H3fAD9IA37GG0 |agency=Associated Press |date=September 17, 2010 |accessdate=September 18, 2010 |title=DA: Paris Hilton to avoid felony in Vegas arrest}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/3143574/No-jail-time-for-Paris-Hilton.html |title=No jail time for Paris Hilton |date=September 18, 2010 |accessdate=September 18, 2010 |publisher=The Sun |location=London |first=Last |last=Updated}}</ref> Clark County District Attorney David Roger said, "If she was arrested for anything besides a minor traffic violation she will spend a year in jail. There will be no discussion. The court will have no discretion."<ref name="AP 2010-09-17" />

On September 21, 2010, on their way to a Tokyo press conference to promote fashion and fragrance lines, Hilton and her sister [[Nicky Hilton|Nicky]] were stopped by immigration officers at [[Narita Airport]] because of Hilton's drug-possession conviction the previous day. Under Japan's strict drug laws, travelers convicted of a drug crime are usually denied entry into the country.<ref name="foxnews.com">{{cite news| url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2010/09/21/paris-hilton-stopped-immigration-japan-airport-report-says/?test=latestnews |publisher=Fox News|title=Paris Hilton Detained at Airport in Japan|date=September 21, 2010}}</ref><ref name="news.sky.com">{{cite news |url=http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/Showbiz-News/Paris-Hilton-Stopped-From-Entering-Japan-By-Immigration-Officials-For-Promotional-Appearance/Article/201009315738506?lpos=Showbiz_News_Carousel_Region_4&lid=ARTICLE_15738506_Paris_Hilton_Stopped_From_Entering_Japan_By_Immigration_Officials_For_Promotional_Appearance |title=Paris Hilton Stopped From Entering Japan By Immigration Officials After Drug Conviction In US |work=Sky News |accessdate=September 13, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100924071703/http://news.sky.com/skynews/Home/Showbiz-News/Paris-Hilton-Stopped-From-Entering-Japan-By-Immigration-Officials-For-Promotional-Appearance/Article/201009315738506?lpos=Showbiz_News_Carousel_Region_4&lid=ARTICLE_15738506_Paris_Hilton_Stopped_From_Entering_Japan_By_Immigration_Officials_For_Promotional_Appearance |archivedate=September 24, 2010 |df= }}</ref> Airport officials questioned Hilton "for hours", and she and Nicky were detained overnight at the airport hotel.<ref name="foxnews.com"/> On September 22 Japanese authorities denied Hilton entry, and she was put on a plane back to the United States. Other stops on their Asian promotional tour were canceled due to [[Indonesia]] and [[Malaysia]]'s anti-drug laws.<ref name="news.sky.com"/>

===Activism===
[[File:Paris Hilton in 2015.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Hilton in 2015]]
As a socialite, Hilton has been a frequent guest at fundraising events around the globe,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/paris-hilton-talks-simple-life-reunion-at-colleagues-spring-luncheon-1103625|title=Paris Hilton Talks 'Simple Life' Reunion at The Colleagues' Spring Luncheon|publisher=}}</ref> and regularly visits children's hospitals and orphanages when she is abroad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/celebrity-heir-and-socialite-paris-hilton-visits-sick-kids-news-photo/95488748|title=Celebrity heir and socialite Paris Hilton visits sick kids at the...|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/english/hollywood/news/Visit-to-orphanage-in-India-changed-my-life-Paris-Hilton/articleshow/48393967.cms |title=Paris Hilton: Visit to orphanage in India changed my life |work=Times of India |date=August 7, 2015 |accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> She has been involved with the [[Starlight Children's Foundation]] and the [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/201411/what-community-service-will-paris-hilton-do|title=What Community Service Will Paris Hilton Do?|date=September 21, 2010|publisher=}}</ref> and is listed on the "First Families" of the [[Children's Hospital Los Angeles]], which means she has donated US$100,000 or more to the hospital.<ref name=chlafirstfamilies>{{cite web|title=First Families|url=http://www.chla.org/first-families|website=Children's Hospital Los Angeles|accessdate=January 1, 2016}}</ref> In 2008, a room at the hospital was named in her honor, and for her charitable efforts, Starlight awarded Hilton, along with mother Kathy and sister Nicky, the 2011 Heart of Gold Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.earthtimes.org/health/paris-hilton-heart-gold-award/499/|title=Paris Hilton given Heart of Gold Award - Health - The Earth Times|first=Andy|last=Tillett|website=www.earthtimes.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hauteliving.com/2011/03/haute-event-paris-nicky-and-kathy-hilton-honored-at-starlight-children%E2%80%99s-foundation-annual-gala/144319/|title=Haute Event: Paris, Nicky, and Kathy Hilton Honored at Starlight Children’s Foundation Annual Gala - Haute Living|date=March 31, 2011|publisher=}}</ref>

In 2011, Hilton  participated in the [[NOH8 Campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.noh8campaign.com/photo-gallery/familiar-faces-part-2/photo/16279 |title=Familiar Faces Part 2 |work=NOH8 Campaign |date=February 1, 2010 |accessdate=November 24, 2018}}</ref> 

In August 2015, Hilton raised US$100,000 for children with disabilities in [[Ibiza]].

In February 2017, Hilton donated 50 of her personal items to the Children’s Hospital Los Angeles and the [[Starlight Children's Foundation]]. In November 2017, she visited [[San Gregorio Atlapulco]], Mexico, where she handed out food and clothes to the damnified families following the [[2017 Central Mexico earthquake]]; she also made a donation of US$350,000 to help rebuild seven different homes that were affected.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etcanada.com/news/269547/paris-hilton-donates-money-to-rebuild-homes-in-earthquake-ravaged-mexico-city/|title=Paris Hilton Donates Money To Rebuild Homes In Earthquake Ravaged Mexico City|first=Aynslee|last=Darmon|date=November 7, 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanidades.com/celebs/paris-hilton-hace-importante-donativo-a-mexico/|title=Paris Hilton hace importante donativo a México - Vanidades|website=www.vanidades.com}}</ref>

In October 2018, Hilton hosted Rock The Runway, an event benefitting [[Children's Miracle Network Hospitals]] and The Sasha Project LA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/paris-hilton-attends-rock-the-runway-presented-by-childrens-news-photo/1052080852|title=Paris Hilton attends Rock The Runway presented by Children's Miracle...|publisher=}}</ref>

===Wealth===
Hilton reportedly earned about US$2 million between 2003 and 2004, US$6.5 million between 2004 and 2005,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2005/53/U3HH.html|title=Paris Hilton, Forbes Top Celebrities|website=www.forbes.com}}</ref> and US$7 million between 2005 and 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2006/53/06celebrities_Paris-Hilton_U3HH.html|title=#56 Paris Hilton - Forbes.com|website=www.forbes.com}}</ref>

In December 2007, Hilton's grandfather [[Barron Hilton]] pledged 97 percent of his estate (the Hilton family fortune) to a charitable organization founded by her great-grandfather [[Conrad N. Hilton]]: the [[Conrad N. Hilton Foundation]].<ref name="PGDC">{{cite web| title = Barron Hilton to Donate 97% of Estate to Hilton Foundation|date = December 26, 2007| publisher = Planned Giving Design Center, LLC| url = http://www.pgdc.com/pgdc/news-story/2007/12/27/barron-hilton-donate-97-estate-hilton-foundation| accessdate = April 2, 2011}}</ref> As a result, his grandchildren's inheritance was reduced.<ref>{{Cite news| first=Peter|last=Walker|author2=Haroon Siddique and agencies|title=Hilton grandfather pledges fortune to charity|date=December 27, 2007| url =https://www.theguardian.com/world/2007/dec/27/usa.haroonsiddique|work=The Guardian|accessdate = December 27, 2007|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news| title=Paris Hilton's Grandfather to Donate a Majority of His Fortune|date=December 27, 2007| url =https://www.nytimes.com/2007/12/27/us/27brfs-HILTON.html?_r=1&ref=us&oref=slogin|work=The New York Times|accessdate = December 27, 2007}}</ref> An immediate pledge of US$1.2&nbsp;billion (proceeds from the sale of Hilton Hotels Corporation) was made, with a further US$1.1&nbsp;billion due after his death.<ref name="PGDC"/> Barron cited the actions of his father, [[Conrad N. Hilton]], as the motivation for his pledge.<ref name="PGDC"/> Conrad (Barron's father) had also left 97 percent of his estate to the foundation, and Barron contested his father's will to regain a sizable amount of the family fortune in a settlement.<ref name="Encyclopedia: Barron Hilton">{{cite web| title = Hilton, William&nbsp;– Overview, Personal Life, Career Details, Social and Economic Impact, Chronology: Hilton, William| publisher = Net Industries| url = http://encyclopedia.jrank.org/articles/pages/6273/Hilton-William.html| format = Encyclopedia| accessdate = April 2, 2011}}</ref>

